2254 llvm::APSInt ConstVal(Context.getTypeSize(Context.getSizeType()));
2255 if (!ArraySize) {
2256 if (ASM == ArrayType::Star)
2257 T = Context.getVariableArrayType(T, nullptr, ASM, Quals, Brackets);
2258 else
2259 T = Context.getIncompleteArrayType(T, ASM, Quals);
2260 } else if (ArraySize->isTypeDependent() || ArraySize->isValueDependent()) {
2261 T = Context.getDependentSizedArrayType(T, ArraySize, ASM, Quals, Brackets);
2262 } else if ((!T->isDependentType() && !T->isIncompleteType() &&
2263 !T->isConstantSizeType()) ||
2264 isArraySizeVLA(*this, ArraySize, ConstVal)) {
2265 // Even in C++11, don't allow contextual conversions in the array bound
2266 // of a VLA.
2267 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
2268 !ArraySize->getType()->isIntegralOrUnscopedEnumerationType()) {
2269 Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_array_size_non_int)
2270 << ArraySize->getType() << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2271 return QualType();
2272 }
2273
2274 // C99: an array with an element type that has a non-constant-size is a VLA.
2275 // C99: an array with a non-ICE size is a VLA. We accept any expression
2276 // that we can fold to a non-zero positive value as an extension.
2277 T = Context.getVariableArrayType(T, ArraySize, ASM, Quals, Brackets);
2278 } else {
2279 // C99 6.7.5.2p1: If the expression is a constant expression, it shall
2280 // have a value greater than zero.
2281 if (ConstVal.isSigned() && ConstVal.isNegative()) {
2282 if (Entity)
2283 Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_decl_negative_array_size)
2284 << getPrintableNameForEntity(Entity) << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2285 else
2286 Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_typecheck_negative_array_size)
2287 << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2288 return QualType();
2289 }
2290 if (ConstVal == 0) {
2291 // GCC accepts zero sized static arrays. We allow them when
2292 // we're not in a SFINAE context.
2293 Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(), isSFINAEContext()
2294 ? diag::err_typecheck_zero_array_size
2295 : diag::ext_typecheck_zero_array_size)
2296 << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2297
2298 if (ASM == ArrayType::Static) {
2299 Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(),
2300 diag::warn_typecheck_zero_static_array_size)
2301 << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2302 ASM = ArrayType::Normal;
2303 }
2304 } else if (!T->isDependentType() && !T->isVariablyModifiedType() &&
2305 !T->isIncompleteType() && !T->isUndeducedType()) {
2306 // Is the array too large?
2307 unsigned ActiveSizeBits
2308 = ConstantArrayType::getNumAddressingBits(Context, T, ConstVal);
2309 if (ActiveSizeBits > ConstantArrayType::getMaxSizeBits(Context)) {
2310 Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_array_too_large)
2311 << ConstVal.toString(10) << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2312 return QualType();
2313 }
2314 }
2315
2316 T = Context.getConstantArrayType(T, ConstVal, ASM, Quals);
2317 }
2318
2319 // OpenCL v1.2 s6.9.d: variable length arrays are not supported.
2320 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL && T->isVariableArrayType()) {
2321 Diag(Loc, diag::err_opencl_vla);
2322 return QualType();
2323 }
2324
2325 if (T->isVariableArrayType() && !Context.getTargetInfo().isVLASupported()) {
2326 // CUDA device code and some other targets don't support VLAs.
2327 targetDiag(Loc, (getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice)
2328 ? diag::err_cuda_vla
2329 : diag::err_vla_unsupported)
2330 << ((getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice)
2331 ? CurrentCUDATarget()
2332 : CFT_InvalidTarget);
2333 }
2334
2335 // If this is not C99, extwarn about VLA's and C99 array size modifiers.
2336 if (!getLangOpts().C99) {
2337 if (T->isVariableArrayType()) {
2338 // Prohibit the use of VLAs during template argument deduction.
2339 if (isSFINAEContext()) {
2340 Diag(Loc, diag::err_vla_in_sfinae);
2341 return QualType();
2342 }
2343 // Just extwarn about VLAs.
2344 else
2345 Diag(Loc, diag::ext_vla);
2346 } else if (ASM != ArrayType::Normal || Quals != 0)
2347 Diag(Loc,
2348 getLangOpts().CPlusPlus? diag::err_c99_array_usage_cxx
2349 : diag::ext_c99_array_usage) << ASM;
2350 }
2351
2352 if (T->isVariableArrayType()) {
2353 // Warn about VLAs for -Wvla.
2354 Diag(Loc, diag::warn_vla_used);
2355 }
2356
2357 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.12.5 - Arrays of blocks are not supported.
2358 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.16.13.1 - Arrays of pipe type are not supported.
2359 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.9.b - Arrays of image/sampler type are not supported.
2360 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
2361 const QualType ArrType = Context.getBaseElementType(T);
2362 if (ArrType->isBlockPointerType() || ArrType->isPipeType() ||
2363 ArrType->isSamplerT() || ArrType->isImageType()) {
2364 Diag(Loc, diag::err_opencl_invalid_type_array) << ArrType;
2365 return QualType();
2366 }
2367 }
2368
2369 return T;
2370}
2371
2372QualType Sema::BuildVectorType(QualType CurType, Expr *SizeExpr,
2373 SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
2374 // The base type must be integer (not Boolean or enumeration) or float, and
2375 // can't already be a vector.
2376 if (!CurType->isDependentType() &&
2377 (!CurType->isBuiltinType() || CurType->isBooleanType() ||
2378 (!CurType->isIntegerType() && !CurType->isRealFloatingType()))) {
2379 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_invalid_vector_type) << CurType;
2380 return QualType();
2381 }
2382
2383 if (SizeExpr->isTypeDependent() || SizeExpr->isValueDependent())
2384 return Context.getDependentVectorType(CurType, SizeExpr, AttrLoc,
2385 VectorType::GenericVector);
2386
2387 llvm::APSInt VecSize(32);
2388 if (!SizeExpr->isIntegerConstantExpr(VecSize, Context)) {
2389 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
2390 << "vector_size" << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
2391 << SizeExpr->getSourceRange();
2392 return QualType();
2393 }
2394
2395 if (CurType->isDependentType())
2396 return Context.getDependentVectorType(CurType, SizeExpr, AttrLoc,
2397 VectorType::GenericVector);
2398
2399 unsigned VectorSize = static_cast<unsigned>(VecSize.getZExtValue() * 8);
2400 unsigned TypeSize = static_cast<unsigned>(Context.getTypeSize(CurType));
2401
2402 if (VectorSize == 0) {
2403 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_zero_size) << SizeExpr->getSourceRange();
2404 return QualType();
2405 }
2406
2407 // vecSize is specified in bytes - convert to bits.
2408 if (VectorSize % TypeSize) {
2409 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_invalid_size)
2410 << SizeExpr->getSourceRange();
2411 return QualType();
2412 }
2413
2414 if (VectorType::isVectorSizeTooLarge(VectorSize / TypeSize)) {
2415 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_size_too_large)
2416 << SizeExpr->getSourceRange();
2417 return QualType();
2418 }
2419
2420 return Context.getVectorType(CurType, VectorSize / TypeSize,
2421 VectorType::GenericVector);
2422}
2423
2424/// Build an ext-vector type.
2425///
2426/// Run the required checks for the extended vector type.
2427QualType Sema::BuildExtVectorType(QualType T, Expr *ArraySize,
2428 SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
2429 // Unlike gcc's vector_size attribute, we do not allow vectors to be defined
2430 // in conjunction with complex types (pointers, arrays, functions, etc.).
2431 //
2432 // Additionally, OpenCL prohibits vectors of booleans (they're considered a
2433 // reserved data type under OpenCL v2.0 s6.1.4), we don't support selects
2434 // on bitvectors, and we have no well-defined ABI for bitvectors, so vectors
2435 // of bool aren't allowed.
2436 if ((!T->isDependentType() && !T->isIntegerType() &&
2437 !T->isRealFloatingType()) ||
2438 T->isBooleanType()) {
2439 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_invalid_vector_type) << T;
2440 return QualType();
2441 }
2442
2443 if (!ArraySize->isTypeDependent() && !ArraySize->isValueDependent()) {
2444 llvm::APSInt vecSize(32);
2445 if (!ArraySize->isIntegerConstantExpr(vecSize, Context)) {
2446 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
2447 << "ext_vector_type" << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
2448 << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2449 return QualType();
2450 }
2451
2452 // Unlike gcc's vector_size attribute, the size is specified as the
2453 // number of elements, not the number of bytes.
2454 unsigned vectorSize = static_cast<unsigned>(vecSize.getZExtValue());
2455
2456 if (vectorSize == 0) {
2457 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_zero_size)
2458 << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2459 return QualType();
2460 }
2461
2462 if (VectorType::isVectorSizeTooLarge(vectorSize)) {
2463 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_size_too_large)
2464 << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2465 return QualType();
2466 }
2467
2468 return Context.getExtVectorType(T, vectorSize);
2469 }
2470
2471 return Context.getDependentSizedExtVectorType(T, ArraySize, AttrLoc);
2472}
2473
2474bool Sema::CheckFunctionReturnType(QualType T, SourceLocation Loc) {
2475 if (T->isArrayType() || T->isFunctionType()) {
2476 Diag(Loc, diag::err_func_returning_array_function)
2477 << T->isFunctionType() << T;
2478 return true;
2479 }
2480
2481 // Functions cannot return half FP.
2482 if (T->isHalfType() && !getLangOpts().HalfArgsAndReturns) {
2483 Diag(Loc, diag::err_parameters_retval_cannot_have_fp16_type) << 1 <<
2484 FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Loc, "*");
2485 return true;
2486 }
2487
2488 // Methods cannot return interface types. All ObjC objects are
2489 // passed by reference.
2490 if (T->isObjCObjectType()) {
2491 Diag(Loc, diag::err_object_cannot_be_passed_returned_by_value)
2492 << 0 << T << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Loc, "*");
2493 return true;
2494 }
2495
2496 return false;
2497}
2498
2499/// Check the extended parameter information. Most of the necessary
2500/// checking should occur when applying the parameter attribute; the
2501/// only other checks required are positional restrictions.
2502static void checkExtParameterInfos(Sema &S, ArrayRef<QualType> paramTypes,
2503 const FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo &EPI,
2504 llvm::function_ref<SourceLocation(unsigned)> getParamLoc) {
2505 assert(EPI.ExtParameterInfos && "shouldn't get here without param infos");
2506
2507 bool hasCheckedSwiftCall = false;
2508 auto checkForSwiftCC = [&](unsigned paramIndex) {
2509 // Only do this once.
2510 if (hasCheckedSwiftCall) return;
2511 hasCheckedSwiftCall = true;
2512 if (EPI.ExtInfo.getCC() == CC_Swift) return;
2513 S.Diag(getParamLoc(paramIndex), diag::err_swift_param_attr_not_swiftcall)
2514 << getParameterABISpelling(EPI.ExtParameterInfos[paramIndex].getABI());
2515 };
2516
2517 for (size_t paramIndex = 0, numParams = paramTypes.size();
2518 paramIndex != numParams; ++paramIndex) {
2519 switch (EPI.ExtParameterInfos[paramIndex].getABI()) {
2520 // Nothing interesting to check for orindary-ABI parameters.
2521 case ParameterABI::Ordinary:
2522 continue;
2523
2524 // swift_indirect_result parameters must be a prefix of the function
2525 // arguments.
2526 case ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult:
2527 checkForSwiftCC(paramIndex);
2528 if (paramIndex != 0 &&
2529 EPI.ExtParameterInfos[paramIndex - 1].getABI()
2530 != ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult) {
2531 S.Diag(getParamLoc(paramIndex),
2532 diag::err_swift_indirect_result_not_first);
2533 }
2534 continue;
2535
2536 case ParameterABI::SwiftContext:
2537 checkForSwiftCC(paramIndex);
2538 continue;
2539
2540 // swift_error parameters must be preceded by a swift_context parameter.
2541 case ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult:
2542 checkForSwiftCC(paramIndex);
2543 if (paramIndex == 0 ||
2544 EPI.ExtParameterInfos[paramIndex - 1].getABI() !=
2545 ParameterABI::SwiftContext) {
2546 S.Diag(getParamLoc(paramIndex),
2547 diag::err_swift_error_result_not_after_swift_context);
2548 }
2549 continue;
2550 }
2551 llvm_unreachable("bad ABI kind");
2552 }
2553}
2554
2555QualType Sema::BuildFunctionType(QualType T,
2556 MutableArrayRef<QualType> ParamTypes,
2557 SourceLocation Loc, DeclarationName Entity,
2558 const FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo &EPI) {
2559 bool Invalid = false;
2560
2561 Invalid |= CheckFunctionReturnType(T, Loc);
2562
2563 for (unsigned Idx = 0, Cnt = ParamTypes.size(); Idx < Cnt; ++Idx) {
2564 // FIXME: Loc is too inprecise here, should use proper locations for args.
2565 QualType ParamType = Context.getAdjustedParameterType(ParamTypes[Idx]);
2566 if (ParamType->isVoidType()) {
2567 Diag(Loc, diag::err_param_with_void_type);
2568 Invalid = true;
2569 } else if (ParamType->isHalfType() && !getLangOpts().HalfArgsAndReturns) {
2570 // Disallow half FP arguments.
2571 Diag(Loc, diag::err_parameters_retval_cannot_have_fp16_type) << 0 <<
2572 FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Loc, "*");
2573 Invalid = true;
2574 }
2575
2576 ParamTypes[Idx] = ParamType;
2577 }
2578
2579 if (EPI.ExtParameterInfos) {
2580 checkExtParameterInfos(*this, ParamTypes, EPI,
2581 [=](unsigned i) { return Loc; });
2582 }
2583
2584 if (EPI.ExtInfo.getProducesResult()) {
2585 // This is just a warning, so we can't fail to build if we see it.
2586 checkNSReturnsRetainedReturnType(Loc, T);
2587 }
2588
2589 if (Invalid)
2590 return QualType();
2591
2592 return Context.getFunctionType(T, ParamTypes, EPI);
2593}
2594
2595/// Build a member pointer type \c T Class::*.
2596///
2597/// \param T the type to which the member pointer refers.
2598/// \param Class the class type into which the member pointer points.
2599/// \param Loc the location where this type begins
2600/// \param Entity the name of the entity that will have this member pointer type
2601///
2602/// \returns a member pointer type, if successful, or a NULL type if there was
2603/// an error.
2604QualType Sema::BuildMemberPointerType(QualType T, QualType Class,
2605 SourceLocation Loc,
2606 DeclarationName Entity) {
2607 // Verify that we're not building a pointer to pointer to function with
2608 // exception specification.
2609 if (CheckDistantExceptionSpec(T)) {
2610 Diag(Loc, diag::err_distant_exception_spec);
2611 return QualType();
2612 }
2613
2614 // C++ 8.3.3p3: A pointer to member shall not point to ... a member
2615 // with reference type, or "cv void."
2616 if (T->isReferenceType()) {
2617 Diag(Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_mempointer_to_reference)
2618 << getPrintableNameForEntity(Entity) << T;
2619 return QualType();
2620 }
2621
2622 if (T->isVoidType()) {
2623 Diag(Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_mempointer_to_void)
2624 << getPrintableNameForEntity(Entity);
2625 return QualType();
2626 }
2627
2628 if (!Class->isDependentType() && !Class->isRecordType()) {
2629 Diag(Loc, diag::err_mempointer_in_nonclass_type) << Class;
2630 return QualType();
2631 }
2632
2633 // Adjust the default free function calling convention to the default method
2634 // calling convention.
2635 bool IsCtorOrDtor =
2636 (Entity.getNameKind() == DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName) ||
2637 (Entity.getNameKind() == DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName);
2638 if (T->isFunctionType())
2639 adjustMemberFunctionCC(T, /*IsStatic=*/false, IsCtorOrDtor, Loc);
2640
2641 return Context.getMemberPointerType(T, Class.getTypePtr());
2642}
2643
2644/// Build a block pointer type.
2645///
2646/// \param T The type to which we'll be building a block pointer.
2647///
2648/// \param Loc The source location, used for diagnostics.
2649///
2650/// \param Entity The name of the entity that involves the block pointer
2651/// type, if known.
2652///
2653/// \returns A suitable block pointer type, if there are no
2654/// errors. Otherwise, returns a NULL type.
2655QualType Sema::BuildBlockPointerType(QualType T,
2656 SourceLocation Loc,
2657 DeclarationName Entity) {
2658 if (!T->isFunctionType()) {
2659 Diag(Loc, diag::err_nonfunction_block_type);
2660 return QualType();
2661 }
2662
2663 if (checkQualifiedFunction(*this, T, Loc, QFK_BlockPointer))
2664 return QualType();
2665
2666 return Context.getBlockPointerType(T);
2667}
2668
2669QualType Sema::GetTypeFromParser(ParsedType Ty, TypeSourceInfo **TInfo) {
2670 QualType QT = Ty.get();
2671 if (QT.isNull()) {
2672 if (TInfo) *TInfo = nullptr;
2673 return QualType();
2674 }
2675
2676 TypeSourceInfo *DI = nullptr;
2677 if (const LocInfoType *LIT = dyn_cast<LocInfoType>(QT)) {
2678 QT = LIT->getType();
2679 DI = LIT->getTypeSourceInfo();
2680 }
2681
2682 if (TInfo) *TInfo = DI;
2683 return QT;
2684}
2685
2686static void transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(TypeProcessingState &state,
2687 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership,
2688 unsigned chunkIndex);
2689
2690/// Given that this is the declaration of a parameter under ARC,
2691/// attempt to infer attributes and such for pointer-to-whatever
2692/// types.
2693static void inferARCWriteback(TypeProcessingState &state,
2694 QualType &declSpecType) {
2695 Sema &S = state.getSema();
2696 Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
2697
2698 // TODO: should we care about decl qualifiers?
2699
2700 // Check whether the declarator has the expected form. We walk
2701 // from the inside out in order to make the block logic work.
2702 unsigned outermostPointerIndex = 0;
2703 bool isBlockPointer = false;
2704 unsigned numPointers = 0;
2705 for (unsigned i = 0, e = declarator.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
2706 unsigned chunkIndex = i;
2707 DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(chunkIndex);
2708 switch (chunk.Kind) {
2709 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
2710 // Ignore parens.
2711 break;
2712
2713 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
2714 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
2715 // Count the number of pointers. Treat references
2716 // interchangeably as pointers; if they're mis-ordered, normal
2717 // type building will discover that.
2718 outermostPointerIndex = chunkIndex;
2719 numPointers++;
2720 break;
2721
2722 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
2723 // If we have a pointer to block pointer, that's an acceptable
2724 // indirect reference; anything else is not an application of
2725 // the rules.
2726 if (numPointers != 1) return;
2727 numPointers++;
2728 outermostPointerIndex = chunkIndex;
2729 isBlockPointer = true;
2730
2731 // We don't care about pointer structure in return values here.
2732 goto done;
2733
2734 case DeclaratorChunk::Array: // suppress if written (id[])?
2735 case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
2736 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
2737 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
2738 return;
2739 }
2740 }
2741 done:
2742
2743 // If we have *one* pointer, then we want to throw the qualifier on
2744 // the declaration-specifiers, which means that it needs to be a
2745 // retainable object type.
2746 if (numPointers == 1) {
2747 // If it's not a retainable object type, the rule doesn't apply.
2748 if (!declSpecType->isObjCRetainableType()) return;
2749
2750 // If it already has lifetime, don't do anything.
2751 if (declSpecType.getObjCLifetime()) return;
2752
2753 // Otherwise, modify the type in-place.
2754 Qualifiers qs;
2755
2756 if (declSpecType->isObjCARCImplicitlyUnretainedType())
2757 qs.addObjCLifetime(Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone);
2758 else
2759 qs.addObjCLifetime(Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing);
2760 declSpecType = S.Context.getQualifiedType(declSpecType, qs);
2761
2762 // If we have *two* pointers, then we want to throw the qualifier on
2763 // the outermost pointer.
2764 } else if (numPointers == 2) {
2765 // If we don't have a block pointer, we need to check whether the
2766 // declaration-specifiers gave us something that will turn into a
2767 // retainable object pointer after we slap the first pointer on it.
2768 if (!isBlockPointer && !declSpecType->isObjCObjectType())
2769 return;
2770
2771 // Look for an explicit lifetime attribute there.
2772 DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(outermostPointerIndex);
2773 if (chunk.Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Pointer &&
2774 chunk.Kind != DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer)
2775 return;
2776 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : chunk.getAttrs())
2777 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership)
2778 return;
2779
2780 transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(state, Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing,
2781 outermostPointerIndex);
2782
2783 // Any other number of pointers/references does not trigger the rule.
2784 } else return;
2785
2786 // TODO: mark whether we did this inference?
2787}
2788
2789void Sema::diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(unsigned DiagID, unsigned Quals,
2790 SourceLocation FallbackLoc,
2791 SourceLocation ConstQualLoc,
2792 SourceLocation VolatileQualLoc,
2793 SourceLocation RestrictQualLoc,
2794 SourceLocation AtomicQualLoc,
2795 SourceLocation UnalignedQualLoc) {
2796 if (!Quals)
2797 return;
2798
2799 struct Qual {
2800 const char *Name;
2801 unsigned Mask;
2802 SourceLocation Loc;
2803 } const QualKinds[5] = {
2804 { "const", DeclSpec::TQ_const, ConstQualLoc },
2805 { "volatile", DeclSpec::TQ_volatile, VolatileQualLoc },
2806 { "restrict", DeclSpec::TQ_restrict, RestrictQualLoc },
2807 { "__unaligned", DeclSpec::TQ_unaligned, UnalignedQualLoc },
2808 { "_Atomic", DeclSpec::TQ_atomic, AtomicQualLoc }
2809 };
2810
2811 SmallString<32> QualStr;
2812 unsigned NumQuals = 0;
2813 SourceLocation Loc;
2814 FixItHint FixIts[5];
2815
2816 // Build a string naming the redundant qualifiers.
2817 for (auto &E : QualKinds) {
2818 if (Quals & E.Mask) {
2819 if (!QualStr.empty()) QualStr += ' ';
2820 QualStr += E.Name;
2821
2822 // If we have a location for the qualifier, offer a fixit.
2823 SourceLocation QualLoc = E.Loc;
2824 if (QualLoc.isValid()) {
2825 FixIts[NumQuals] = FixItHint::CreateRemoval(QualLoc);
2826 if (Loc.isInvalid() ||
2827 getSourceManager().isBeforeInTranslationUnit(QualLoc, Loc))
2828 Loc = QualLoc;
2829 }
2830
2831 ++NumQuals;
2832 }
2833 }
2834
2835 Diag(Loc.isInvalid() ? FallbackLoc : Loc, DiagID)
2836 << QualStr << NumQuals << FixIts[0] << FixIts[1] << FixIts[2] << FixIts[3];
2837}
2838
2839// Diagnose pointless type qualifiers on the return type of a function.
2840static void diagnoseRedundantReturnTypeQualifiers(Sema &S, QualType RetTy,
2841 Declarator &D,
2842 unsigned FunctionChunkIndex) {
2843 if (D.getTypeObject(FunctionChunkIndex).Fun.hasTrailingReturnType()) {
2844 // FIXME: TypeSourceInfo doesn't preserve location information for
2845 // qualifiers.
2846 S.diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(diag::warn_qual_return_type,
2847 RetTy.getLocalCVRQualifiers(),
2848 D.getIdentifierLoc());
2849 return;
2850 }
2851
2852 for (unsigned OuterChunkIndex = FunctionChunkIndex + 1,
2853 End = D.getNumTypeObjects();
2854 OuterChunkIndex != End; ++OuterChunkIndex) {
2855 DeclaratorChunk &OuterChunk = D.getTypeObject(OuterChunkIndex);
2856 switch (OuterChunk.Kind) {
2857 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
2858 continue;
2859
2860 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer: {
2861 DeclaratorChunk::PointerTypeInfo &PTI = OuterChunk.Ptr;
2862 S.diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(
2863 diag::warn_qual_return_type,
2864 PTI.TypeQuals,
2865 SourceLocation(),
2866 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(PTI.ConstQualLoc),
2867 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(PTI.VolatileQualLoc),
2868 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(PTI.RestrictQualLoc),
2869 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(PTI.AtomicQualLoc),
2870 SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(PTI.UnalignedQualLoc));
2871 return;
2872 }
2873
2874 case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
2875 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
2876 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
2877 case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
2878 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
2879 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
2880 // FIXME: We can't currently provide an accurate source location and a
2881 // fix-it hint for these.
2882 unsigned AtomicQual = RetTy->isAtomicType() ? DeclSpec::TQ_atomic : 0;
2883 S.diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(diag::warn_qual_return_type,
2884 RetTy.getCVRQualifiers() | AtomicQual,
2885 D.getIdentifierLoc());
2886 return;
2887 }
2888
2889 llvm_unreachable("unknown declarator chunk kind");
2890 }
2891
2892 // If the qualifiers come from a conversion function type, don't diagnose
2893 // them -- they're not necessarily redundant, since such a conversion
2894 // operator can be explicitly called as "x.operator const int()".
2895 if (D.getName().getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConversionFunctionId)
2896 return;
2897
2898 // Just parens all the way out to the decl specifiers. Diagnose any qualifiers
2899 // which are present there.
2900 S.diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(diag::warn_qual_return_type,
2901 D.getDeclSpec().getTypeQualifiers(),
2902 D.getIdentifierLoc(),
2903 D.getDeclSpec().getConstSpecLoc(),
2904 D.getDeclSpec().getVolatileSpecLoc(),
2905 D.getDeclSpec().getRestrictSpecLoc(),
2906 D.getDeclSpec().getAtomicSpecLoc(),
2907 D.getDeclSpec().getUnalignedSpecLoc());
2908}
2909
2910static QualType GetDeclSpecTypeForDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &state,
2911 TypeSourceInfo *&ReturnTypeInfo) {
2912 Sema &SemaRef = state.getSema();
2913 Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
2914 QualType T;
2915 ReturnTypeInfo = nullptr;
2916
2917 // The TagDecl owned by the DeclSpec.
2918 TagDecl *OwnedTagDecl = nullptr;
2919
2920 switch (D.getName().getKind()) {
2921 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ImplicitSelfParam:
2922 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_OperatorFunctionId:
2923 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier:
2924 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_LiteralOperatorId:
2925 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_TemplateId:
2926 T = ConvertDeclSpecToType(state);
2927
2928 if (!D.isInvalidType() && D.getDeclSpec().isTypeSpecOwned()) {
2929 OwnedTagDecl = cast<TagDecl>(D.getDeclSpec().getRepAsDecl());
2930 // Owned declaration is embedded in declarator.
2931 OwnedTagDecl->setEmbeddedInDeclarator(true);
2932 }
2933 break;
2934
2935 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConstructorName:
2936 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConstructorTemplateId:
2937 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_DestructorName:
2938 // Constructors and destructors don't have return types. Use
2939 // "void" instead.
2940 T = SemaRef.Context.VoidTy;
2941 processTypeAttrs(state, T, TAL_DeclSpec,
2942 D.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes());
2943 break;
2944
2945 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_DeductionGuideName:
2946 // Deduction guides have a trailing return type and no type in their
2947 // decl-specifier sequence. Use a placeholder return type for now.
2948 T = SemaRef.Context.DependentTy;
2949 break;
2950
2951 case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConversionFunctionId:
2952 // The result type of a conversion function is the type that it
2953 // converts to.
2954 T = SemaRef.GetTypeFromParser(D.getName().ConversionFunctionId,
2955 &ReturnTypeInfo);
2956 break;
2957 }
2958
2959 if (!D.getAttributes().empty())
2960 distributeTypeAttrsFromDeclarator(state, T);
2961
2962 // C++11 [dcl.spec.auto]p5: reject 'auto' if it is not in an allowed context.
2963 if (DeducedType *Deduced = T->getContainedDeducedType()) {
2964 AutoType *Auto = dyn_cast<AutoType>(Deduced);
2965 int Error = -1;
2966
2967 // Is this a 'auto' or 'decltype(auto)' type (as opposed to __auto_type or
2968 // class template argument deduction)?
2969 bool IsCXXAutoType =
2970 (Auto && Auto->getKeyword() != AutoTypeKeyword::GNUAutoType);
2971 bool IsDeducedReturnType = false;
2972
2973 switch (D.getContext()) {
2974 case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprContext:
2975 // Declared return type of a lambda-declarator is implicit and is always
2976 // 'auto'.
2977 break;
2978 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameterContext:
2979 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCResultContext:
2980 case DeclaratorContext::PrototypeContext:
2981 Error = 0;
2982 break;
2983 case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameterContext:
2984 // In C++14, generic lambdas allow 'auto' in their parameters.
2985 if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 ||
2986 !Auto || Auto->getKeyword() != AutoTypeKeyword::Auto)
2987 Error = 16;
2988 else {
2989 // If auto is mentioned in a lambda parameter context, convert it to a
2990 // template parameter type.
2991 sema::LambdaScopeInfo *LSI = SemaRef.getCurLambda();
2992 assert(LSI && "No LambdaScopeInfo on the stack!");
2993 const unsigned TemplateParameterDepth = LSI->AutoTemplateParameterDepth;
2994 const unsigned AutoParameterPosition = LSI->TemplateParams.size();
2995 const bool IsParameterPack = D.hasEllipsis();
2996
2997 // Create the TemplateTypeParmDecl here to retrieve the corresponding
2998 // template parameter type. Template parameters are temporarily added
2999 // to the TU until the associated TemplateDecl is created.
3000 TemplateTypeParmDecl *CorrespondingTemplateParam =
3001 TemplateTypeParmDecl::Create(
3002 SemaRef.Context, SemaRef.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl(),
3003 /*KeyLoc*/ SourceLocation(), /*NameLoc*/ D.getBeginLoc(),
3004 TemplateParameterDepth, AutoParameterPosition,
3005 /*Identifier*/ nullptr, false, IsParameterPack);
3006 CorrespondingTemplateParam->setImplicit();
3007 LSI->TemplateParams.push_back(CorrespondingTemplateParam);
3008 // Replace the 'auto' in the function parameter with this invented
3009 // template type parameter.
3010 // FIXME: Retain some type sugar to indicate that this was written
3011 // as 'auto'.
3012 T = state.ReplaceAutoType(
3013 T, QualType(CorrespondingTemplateParam->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
3014 }
3015 break;
3016 case DeclaratorContext::MemberContext: {
3017 if (D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::SCS_static ||
3018 D.isFunctionDeclarator())
3019 break;
3020 bool Cxx = SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus;
3021 switch (cast<TagDecl>(SemaRef.CurContext)->getTagKind()) {
3022 case TTK_Enum: llvm_unreachable("unhandled tag kind");
3023 case TTK_Struct: Error = Cxx ? 1 : 2; /* Struct member */ break;
3024 case TTK_Union: Error = Cxx ? 3 : 4; /* Union member */ break;
3025 case TTK_Class: Error = 5; /* Class member */ break;
3026 case TTK_Interface: Error = 6; /* Interface member */ break;
3027 }
3028 if (D.getDeclSpec().isFriendSpecified())
3029 Error = 20; // Friend type
3030 break;
3031 }
3032 case DeclaratorContext::CXXCatchContext:
3033 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCCatchContext:
3034 Error = 7; // Exception declaration
3035 break;
3036 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateParamContext:
3037 if (isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced))
3038 Error = 19; // Template parameter
3039 else if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17)
3040 Error = 8; // Template parameter (until C++17)
3041 break;
3042 case DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteralContext:
3043 Error = 9; // Block literal
3044 break;
3045 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateArgContext:
3046 // Within a template argument list, a deduced template specialization
3047 // type will be reinterpreted as a template template argument.
3048 if (isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced) &&
3049 !D.getNumTypeObjects() &&
3050 D.getDeclSpec().getParsedSpecifiers() == DeclSpec::PQ_TypeSpecifier)
3051 break;
3052 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3053 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArgContext:
3054 Error = 10; // Template type argument
3055 break;
3056 case DeclaratorContext::AliasDeclContext:
3057 case DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplateContext:
3058 Error = 12; // Type alias
3059 break;
3060 case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnContext:
3061 case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnVarContext:
3062 if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 || !IsCXXAutoType)
3063 Error = 13; // Function return type
3064 IsDeducedReturnType = true;
3065 break;
3066 case DeclaratorContext::ConversionIdContext:
3067 if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 || !IsCXXAutoType)
3068 Error = 14; // conversion-type-id
3069 IsDeducedReturnType = true;
3070 break;
3071 case DeclaratorContext::FunctionalCastContext:
3072 if (isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced))
3073 break;
3074 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3075 case DeclaratorContext::TypeNameContext:
3076 Error = 15; // Generic
3077 break;
3078 case DeclaratorContext::FileContext:
3079 case DeclaratorContext::BlockContext:
3080 case DeclaratorContext::ForContext:
3081 case DeclaratorContext::InitStmtContext:
3082 case DeclaratorContext::ConditionContext:
3083 // FIXME: P0091R3 (erroneously) does not permit class template argument
3084 // deduction in conditions, for-init-statements, and other declarations
3085 // that are not simple-declarations.
3086 break;
3087 case DeclaratorContext::CXXNewContext:
3088 // FIXME: P0091R3 does not permit class template argument deduction here,
3089 // but we follow GCC and allow it anyway.
3090 if (!IsCXXAutoType && !isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced))
3091 Error = 17; // 'new' type
3092 break;
3093 case DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeListContext:
3094 Error = 18; // K&R function parameter
3095 break;
3096 }
3097
3098 if (D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::SCS_typedef)
3099 Error = 11;
3100
3101 // In Objective-C it is an error to use 'auto' on a function declarator
3102 // (and everywhere for '__auto_type').
3103 if (D.isFunctionDeclarator() &&
3104 (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 || !IsCXXAutoType))
3105 Error = 13;
3106
3107 bool HaveTrailing = false;
3108
3109 // C++11 [dcl.spec.auto]p2: 'auto' is always fine if the declarator
3110 // contains a trailing return type. That is only legal at the outermost
3111 // level. Check all declarator chunks (outermost first) anyway, to give
3112 // better diagnostics.
3113 // We don't support '__auto_type' with trailing return types.
3114 // FIXME: Should we only do this for 'auto' and not 'decltype(auto)'?
3115 if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && IsCXXAutoType &&
3116 D.hasTrailingReturnType()) {
3117 HaveTrailing = true;
3118 Error = -1;
3119 }
3120
3121 SourceRange AutoRange = D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc();
3122 if (D.getName().getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConversionFunctionId)
3123 AutoRange = D.getName().getSourceRange();
3124
3125 if (Error != -1) {
3126 unsigned Kind;
3127 if (Auto) {
3128 switch (Auto->getKeyword()) {
3129 case AutoTypeKeyword::Auto: Kind = 0; break;
3130 case AutoTypeKeyword::DecltypeAuto: Kind = 1; break;
3131 case AutoTypeKeyword::GNUAutoType: Kind = 2; break;
3132 }
3133 } else {
3134 assert(isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced) &&
3135 "unknown auto type");
3136 Kind = 3;
3137 }
3138
3139 auto *DTST = dyn_cast<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced);
3140 TemplateName TN = DTST ? DTST->getTemplateName() : TemplateName();
3141
3142 SemaRef.Diag(AutoRange.getBegin(), diag::err_auto_not_allowed)
3143 << Kind << Error << (int)SemaRef.getTemplateNameKindForDiagnostics(TN)
3144 << QualType(Deduced, 0) << AutoRange;
3145 if (auto *TD = TN.getAsTemplateDecl())
3146 SemaRef.Diag(TD->getLocation(), diag::note_template_decl_here);
3147
3148 T = SemaRef.Context.IntTy;
3149 D.setInvalidType(true);
3150 } else if (!HaveTrailing &&
3151 D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprContext) {
3152 // If there was a trailing return type, we already got
3153 // warn_cxx98_compat_trailing_return_type in the parser.
3154 SemaRef.Diag(AutoRange.getBegin(),
3155 D.getContext() ==
3156 DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameterContext
3157 ? diag::warn_cxx11_compat_generic_lambda
3158 : IsDeducedReturnType
3159 ? diag::warn_cxx11_compat_deduced_return_type
3160 : diag::warn_cxx98_compat_auto_type_specifier)
3161 << AutoRange;
3162 }
3163 }
3164
3165 if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
3166 OwnedTagDecl && OwnedTagDecl->isCompleteDefinition()) {
3167 // Check the contexts where C++ forbids the declaration of a new class
3168 // or enumeration in a type-specifier-seq.
3169 unsigned DiagID = 0;
3170 switch (D.getContext()) {
3171 case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnContext:
3172 case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnVarContext:
3173 // Class and enumeration definitions are syntactically not allowed in
3174 // trailing return types.
3175 llvm_unreachable("parser should not have allowed this");
3176 break;
3177 case DeclaratorContext::FileContext:
3178 case DeclaratorContext::MemberContext:
3179 case DeclaratorContext::BlockContext:
3180 case DeclaratorContext::ForContext:
3181 case DeclaratorContext::InitStmtContext:
3182 case DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteralContext:
3183 case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprContext:
3184 // C++11 [dcl.type]p3:
3185 // A type-specifier-seq shall not define a class or enumeration unless
3186 // it appears in the type-id of an alias-declaration (7.1.3) that is not
3187 // the declaration of a template-declaration.
3188 case DeclaratorContext::AliasDeclContext:
3189 break;
3190 case DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplateContext:
3191 DiagID = diag::err_type_defined_in_alias_template;
3192 break;
3193 case DeclaratorContext::TypeNameContext:
3194 case DeclaratorContext::FunctionalCastContext:
3195 case DeclaratorContext::ConversionIdContext:
3196 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateParamContext:
3197 case DeclaratorContext::CXXNewContext:
3198 case DeclaratorContext::CXXCatchContext:
3199 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCCatchContext:
3200 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateArgContext:
3201 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArgContext:
3202 DiagID = diag::err_type_defined_in_type_specifier;
3203 break;
3204 case DeclaratorContext::PrototypeContext:
3205 case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameterContext:
3206 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameterContext:
3207 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCResultContext:
3208 case DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeListContext:
3209 // C++ [dcl.fct]p6:
3210 // Types shall not be defined in return or parameter types.
3211 DiagID = diag::err_type_defined_in_param_type;
3212 break;
3213 case DeclaratorContext::ConditionContext:
3214 // C++ 6.4p2:
3215 // The type-specifier-seq shall not contain typedef and shall not declare
3216 // a new class or enumeration.
3217 DiagID = diag::err_type_defined_in_condition;
3218 break;
3219 }
3220
3221 if (DiagID != 0) {
3222 SemaRef.Diag(OwnedTagDecl->getLocation(), DiagID)
3223 << SemaRef.Context.getTypeDeclType(OwnedTagDecl);
3224 D.setInvalidType(true);
3225 }
3226 }
3227
3228 assert(!T.isNull() && "This function should not return a null type");
3229 return T;
3230}
3231
3232/// Produce an appropriate diagnostic for an ambiguity between a function
3233/// declarator and a C++ direct-initializer.
3234static void warnAboutAmbiguousFunction(Sema &S, Declarator &D,
3235 DeclaratorChunk &DeclType, QualType RT) {
3236 const DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI = DeclType.Fun;
3237 assert(FTI.isAmbiguous && "no direct-initializer / function ambiguity");
3238
3239 // If the return type is void there is no ambiguity.
3240 if (RT->isVoidType())
3241 return;
3242
3243 // An initializer for a non-class type can have at most one argument.
3244 if (!RT->isRecordType() && FTI.NumParams > 1)
3245 return;
3246
3247 // An initializer for a reference must have exactly one argument.
3248 if (RT->isReferenceType() && FTI.NumParams != 1)
3249 return;
3250
3251 // Only warn if this declarator is declaring a function at block scope, and
3252 // doesn't have a storage class (such as 'extern') specified.
3253 if (!D.isFunctionDeclarator() ||
3254 D.getFunctionDefinitionKind() != FDK_Declaration ||
3255 !S.CurContext->isFunctionOrMethod() ||
3256 D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec()
3257 != DeclSpec::SCS_unspecified)
3258 return;
3259
3260 // Inside a condition, a direct initializer is not permitted. We allow one to
3261 // be parsed in order to give better diagnostics in condition parsing.
3262 if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::ConditionContext)
3263 return;
3264
3265 SourceRange ParenRange(DeclType.Loc, DeclType.EndLoc);
3266
3267 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc,
3268 FTI.NumParams ? diag::warn_parens_disambiguated_as_function_declaration
3269 : diag::warn_empty_parens_are_function_decl)
3270 << ParenRange;
3271
3272 // If the declaration looks like:
3273 // T var1,
3274 // f();
3275 // and name lookup finds a function named 'f', then the ',' was
3276 // probably intended to be a ';'.
3277 if (!D.isFirstDeclarator() && D.getIdentifier()) {
3278 FullSourceLoc Comma(D.getCommaLoc(), S.SourceMgr);
3279 FullSourceLoc Name(D.getIdentifierLoc(), S.SourceMgr);
3280 if (Comma.getFileID() != Name.getFileID() ||
3281 Comma.getSpellingLineNumber() != Name.getSpellingLineNumber()) {
3282 LookupResult Result(S, D.getIdentifier(), SourceLocation(),
3283 Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
3284 if (S.LookupName(Result, S.getCurScope()))
3285 S.Diag(D.getCommaLoc(), diag::note_empty_parens_function_call)
3286 << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(D.getCommaLoc(), ";")
3287 << D.getIdentifier();
3288 Result.suppressDiagnostics();
3289 }
3290 }
3291
3292 if (FTI.NumParams > 0) {
3293 // For a declaration with parameters, eg. "T var(T());", suggest adding
3294 // parens around the first parameter to turn the declaration into a
3295 // variable declaration.
3296 SourceRange Range = FTI.Params[0].Param->getSourceRange();
3297 SourceLocation B = Range.getBegin();
3298 SourceLocation E = S.getLocForEndOfToken(Range.getEnd());
3299 // FIXME: Maybe we should suggest adding braces instead of parens
3300 // in C++11 for classes that don't have an initializer_list constructor.
3301 S.Diag(B, diag::note_additional_parens_for_variable_declaration)
3302 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(B, "(")
3303 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(E, ")");
3304 } else {
3305 // For a declaration without parameters, eg. "T var();", suggest replacing
3306 // the parens with an initializer to turn the declaration into a variable
3307 // declaration.
3308 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = RT->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3309
3310 // Empty parens mean value-initialization, and no parens mean
3311 // default initialization. These are equivalent if the default
3312 // constructor is user-provided or if zero-initialization is a
3313 // no-op.
3314 if (RD && RD->hasDefinition() &&
3315 (RD->isEmpty() || RD->hasUserProvidedDefaultConstructor()))
3316 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::note_empty_parens_default_ctor)
3317 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(ParenRange);
3318 else {
3319 std::string Init =
3320 S.getFixItZeroInitializerForType(RT, ParenRange.getBegin());
3321 if (Init.empty() && S.LangOpts.CPlusPlus11)
3322 Init = "{}";
3323 if (!Init.empty())
3324 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::note_empty_parens_zero_initialize)
3325 << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(ParenRange, Init);
3326 }
3327 }
3328}
3329
3330/// Produce an appropriate diagnostic for a declarator with top-level
3331/// parentheses.
3332static void warnAboutRedundantParens(Sema &S, Declarator &D, QualType T) {
3333 DeclaratorChunk &Paren = D.getTypeObject(D.getNumTypeObjects() - 1);
3334 assert(Paren.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Paren &&
3335 "do not have redundant top-level parentheses");
3336
3337 // This is a syntactic check; we're not interested in cases that arise
3338 // during template instantiation.
3339 if (S.inTemplateInstantiation())
3340 return;
3341
3342 // Check whether this could be intended to be a construction of a temporary
3343 // object in C++ via a function-style cast.
3344 bool CouldBeTemporaryObject =
3345 S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && D.isExpressionContext() &&
3346 !D.isInvalidType() && D.getIdentifier() &&
3347 D.getDeclSpec().getParsedSpecifiers() == DeclSpec::PQ_TypeSpecifier &&
3348 (T->isRecordType() || T->isDependentType()) &&
3349 D.getDeclSpec().getTypeQualifiers() == 0 && D.isFirstDeclarator();
3350
3351 bool StartsWithDeclaratorId = true;
3352 for (auto &C : D.type_objects()) {
3353 switch (C.Kind) {
3354 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
3355 if (&C == &Paren)
3356 continue;
3357 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3358 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
3359 StartsWithDeclaratorId = false;
3360 continue;
3361
3362 case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
3363 if (!C.Arr.NumElts)
3364 CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3365 continue;
3366
3367 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
3368 // FIXME: Suppress the warning here if there is no initializer; we're
3369 // going to give an error anyway.
3370 // We assume that something like 'T (&x) = y;' is highly likely to not
3371 // be intended to be a temporary object.
3372 CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3373 StartsWithDeclaratorId = false;
3374 continue;
3375
3376 case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
3377 // In a new-type-id, function chunks require parentheses.
3378 if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::CXXNewContext)
3379 return;
3380 // FIXME: "A(f())" deserves a vexing-parse warning, not just a
3381 // redundant-parens warning, but we don't know whether the function
3382 // chunk was syntactically valid as an expression here.
3383 CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3384 continue;
3385
3386 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
3387 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
3388 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
3389 // These cannot appear in expressions.
3390 CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3391 StartsWithDeclaratorId = false;
3392 continue;
3393 }
3394 }
3395
3396 // FIXME: If there is an initializer, assume that this is not intended to be
3397 // a construction of a temporary object.
3398
3399 // Check whether the name has already been declared; if not, this is not a
3400 // function-style cast.
3401 if (CouldBeTemporaryObject) {
3402 LookupResult Result(S, D.getIdentifier(), SourceLocation(),
3403 Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
3404 if (!S.LookupName(Result, S.getCurScope()))
3405 CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3406 Result.suppressDiagnostics();
3407 }
3408
3409 SourceRange ParenRange(Paren.Loc, Paren.EndLoc);
3410
3411 if (!CouldBeTemporaryObject) {
3412 // If we have A (::B), the parentheses affect the meaning of the program.
3413 // Suppress the warning in that case. Don't bother looking at the DeclSpec
3414 // here: even (e.g.) "int ::x" is visually ambiguous even though it's
3415 // formally unambiguous.
3416 if (StartsWithDeclaratorId && D.getCXXScopeSpec().isValid()) {
3417 for (NestedNameSpecifier *NNS = D.getCXXScopeSpec().getScopeRep(); NNS;
3418 NNS = NNS->getPrefix()) {
3419 if (NNS->getKind() == NestedNameSpecifier::Global)
3420 return;
3421 }
3422 }
3423
3424 S.Diag(Paren.Loc, diag::warn_redundant_parens_around_declarator)
3425 << ParenRange << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Paren.Loc)
3426 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Paren.EndLoc);
3427 return;
3428 }
3429
3430 S.Diag(Paren.Loc, diag::warn_parens_disambiguated_as_variable_declaration)
3431 << ParenRange << D.getIdentifier();
3432 auto *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3433 if (!RD || !RD->hasDefinition() || RD->hasNonTrivialDestructor())
3434 S.Diag(Paren.Loc, diag::note_raii_guard_add_name)
3435 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Paren.Loc, " varname") << T
3436 << D.getIdentifier();
3437 // FIXME: A cast to void is probably a better suggestion in cases where it's
3438 // valid (when there is no initializer and we're not in a condition).
3439 S.Diag(D.getBeginLoc(), diag::note_function_style_cast_add_parentheses)
3440 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(D.getBeginLoc(), "(")
3441 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(S.getLocForEndOfToken(D.getEndLoc()), ")");
3442 S.Diag(Paren.Loc, diag::note_remove_parens_for_variable_declaration)
3443 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Paren.Loc)
3444 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Paren.EndLoc);
3445}
3446
3447/// Helper for figuring out the default CC for a function declarator type. If
3448/// this is the outermost chunk, then we can determine the CC from the
3449/// declarator context. If not, then this could be either a member function
3450/// type or normal function type.
3451static CallingConv getCCForDeclaratorChunk(
3452 Sema &S, Declarator &D, const ParsedAttributesView &AttrList,
3453 const DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI, unsigned ChunkIndex) {
3454 assert(D.getTypeObject(ChunkIndex).Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Function);
3455
3456 // Check for an explicit CC attribute.
3457 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : AttrList) {
3458 switch (AL.getKind()) {
3459 CALLING_CONV_ATTRS_CASELIST : {
3460 // Ignore attributes that don't validate or can't apply to the
3461 // function type. We'll diagnose the failure to apply them in
3462 // handleFunctionTypeAttr.
3463 CallingConv CC;
3464 if (!S.CheckCallingConvAttr(AL, CC) &&
3465 (!FTI.isVariadic || supportsVariadicCall(CC))) {
3466 return CC;
3467 }
3468 break;
3469 }
3470
3471 default:
3472 break;
3473 }
3474 }
3475
3476 bool IsCXXInstanceMethod = false;
3477
3478 if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
3479 // Look inwards through parentheses to see if this chunk will form a
3480 // member pointer type or if we're the declarator. Any type attributes
3481 // between here and there will override the CC we choose here.
3482 unsigned I = ChunkIndex;
3483 bool FoundNonParen = false;
3484 while (I && !FoundNonParen) {
3485 --I;
3486 if (D.getTypeObject(I).Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Paren)
3487 FoundNonParen = true;
3488 }
3489
3490 if (FoundNonParen) {
3491 // If we're not the declarator, we're a regular function type unless we're
3492 // in a member pointer.
3493 IsCXXInstanceMethod =
3494 D.getTypeObject(I).Kind == DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer;
3495 } else if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprContext) {
3496 // This can only be a call operator for a lambda, which is an instance
3497 // method.
3498 IsCXXInstanceMethod = true;
3499 } else {
3500 // We're the innermost decl chunk, so must be a function declarator.
3501 assert(D.isFunctionDeclarator());
3502
3503 // If we're inside a record, we're declaring a method, but it could be
3504 // explicitly or implicitly static.
3505 IsCXXInstanceMethod =
3506 D.isFirstDeclarationOfMember() &&
3507 D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() != DeclSpec::SCS_typedef &&
3508 !D.isStaticMember();
3509 }
3510 }
3511
3512 CallingConv CC = S.Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(FTI.isVariadic,
3513 IsCXXInstanceMethod);
3514
3515 // Attribute AT_OpenCLKernel affects the calling convention for SPIR
3516 // and AMDGPU targets, hence it cannot be treated as a calling
3517 // convention attribute. This is the simplest place to infer
3518 // calling convention for OpenCL kernels.
3519 if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
3520 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : D.getDeclSpec().getAttributes()) {
3521 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLKernel) {
3522 CC = CC_OpenCLKernel;
3523 break;
3524 }
3525 }
3526 }
3527
3528 return CC;
3529}

3531namespace {
3532 /// A simple notion of pointer kinds, which matches up with the various
3533 /// pointer declarators.
3534 enum class SimplePointerKind {
3535 Pointer,
3536 BlockPointer,
3537 MemberPointer,
3538 Array,
3539 };
3540} // end anonymous namespace
3541
3542IdentifierInfo *Sema::getNullabilityKeyword(NullabilityKind nullability) {
3543 switch (nullability) {
3544 case NullabilityKind::NonNull:
3545 if (!Ident__Nonnull)
3546 Ident__Nonnull = PP.getIdentifierInfo("_Nonnull");
3547 return Ident__Nonnull;
3548
3549 case NullabilityKind::Nullable:
3550 if (!Ident__Nullable)
3551 Ident__Nullable = PP.getIdentifierInfo("_Nullable");
3552 return Ident__Nullable;
3553
3554 case NullabilityKind::Unspecified:
3555 if (!Ident__Null_unspecified)
3556 Ident__Null_unspecified = PP.getIdentifierInfo("_Null_unspecified");
3557 return Ident__Null_unspecified;
3558 }
3559 llvm_unreachable("Unknown nullability kind.");
3560}
3561
3562/// Retrieve the identifier "NSError".
3563IdentifierInfo *Sema::getNSErrorIdent() {
3564 if (!Ident_NSError)
3565 Ident_NSError = PP.getIdentifierInfo("NSError");
3566
3567 return Ident_NSError;
3568}
3569
3570/// Check whether there is a nullability attribute of any kind in the given
3571/// attribute list.
3572static bool hasNullabilityAttr(const ParsedAttributesView &attrs) {
3573 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : attrs) {
3574 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNonNull ||
3575 AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullable ||
3576 AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullUnspecified)
3577 return true;
3578 }
3579
3580 return false;
3581}
3582
3583namespace {
3584 /// Describes the kind of a pointer a declarator describes.
3585 enum class PointerDeclaratorKind {
3586 // Not a pointer.
3587 NonPointer,
3588 // Single-level pointer.
3589 SingleLevelPointer,
3590 // Multi-level pointer (of any pointer kind).
3591 MultiLevelPointer,
3592 // CFFooRef*
3593 MaybePointerToCFRef,
3594 // CFErrorRef*
3595 CFErrorRefPointer,
3596 // NSError**
3597 NSErrorPointerPointer,
3598 };
3599
3600 /// Describes a declarator chunk wrapping a pointer that marks inference as
3601 /// unexpected.
3602 // These values must be kept in sync with diagnostics.
3603 enum class PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind {
3604 /// Pointer is top-level.
3605 None = -1,
3606 /// Pointer is an array element.
3607 Array = 0,
3608 /// Pointer is the referent type of a C++ reference.
3609 Reference = 1
3610 };
3611} // end anonymous namespace
3612
3613/// Classify the given declarator, whose type-specified is \c type, based on
3614/// what kind of pointer it refers to.
3615///
3616/// This is used to determine the default nullability.
3617static PointerDeclaratorKind
3618classifyPointerDeclarator(Sema &S, QualType type, Declarator &declarator,
3619 PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind &wrappingKind) {
3620 unsigned numNormalPointers = 0;
3621
3622 // For any dependent type, we consider it a non-pointer.
3623 if (type->isDependentType())
3624 return PointerDeclaratorKind::NonPointer;
3625
3626 // Look through the declarator chunks to identify pointers.
3627 for (unsigned i = 0, n = declarator.getNumTypeObjects(); i != n; ++i) {
3628 DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(i);
3629 switch (chunk.Kind) {
3630 case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
3631 if (numNormalPointers == 0)
3632 wrappingKind = PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::Array;
3633 break;
3634
3635 case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
3636 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
3637 break;
3638
3639 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
3640 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
3641 return numNormalPointers > 0 ? PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer
3642 : PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer;
3643
3644 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
3645 break;
3646
3647 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
3648 if (numNormalPointers == 0)
3649 wrappingKind = PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::Reference;
3650 break;
3651
3652 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
3653 ++numNormalPointers;
3654 if (numNormalPointers > 2)
3655 return PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer;
3656 break;
3657 }
3658 }
3659
3660 // Then, dig into the type specifier itself.
3661 unsigned numTypeSpecifierPointers = 0;
3662 do {
3663 // Decompose normal pointers.
3664 if (auto ptrType = type->getAs<PointerType>()) {
3665 ++numNormalPointers;
3666
3667 if (numNormalPointers > 2)
3668 return PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer;
3669
3670 type = ptrType->getPointeeType();
3671 ++numTypeSpecifierPointers;
3672 continue;
3673 }
3674
3675 // Decompose block pointers.
3676 if (type->getAs<BlockPointerType>()) {
3677 return numNormalPointers > 0 ? PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer
3678 : PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer;
3679 }
3680
3681 // Decompose member pointers.
3682 if (type->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) {
3683 return numNormalPointers > 0 ? PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer
3684 : PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer;
3685 }
3686
3687 // Look at Objective-C object pointers.
3688 if (auto objcObjectPtr = type->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
3689 ++numNormalPointers;
3690 ++numTypeSpecifierPointers;
3691
3692 // If this is NSError**, report that.
3693 if (auto objcClassDecl = objcObjectPtr->getInterfaceDecl()) {
3694 if (objcClassDecl->getIdentifier() == S.getNSErrorIdent() &&
3695 numNormalPointers == 2 && numTypeSpecifierPointers < 2) {
3696 return PointerDeclaratorKind::NSErrorPointerPointer;
3697 }
3698 }
3699
3700 break;
3701 }
3702
3703 // Look at Objective-C class types.
3704 if (auto objcClass = type->getAs<ObjCInterfaceType>()) {
3705 if (objcClass->getInterface()->getIdentifier() == S.getNSErrorIdent()) {
3706 if (numNormalPointers == 2 && numTypeSpecifierPointers < 2)
3707 return PointerDeclaratorKind::NSErrorPointerPointer;
3708 }
3709
3710 break;
3711 }
3712
3713 // If at this point we haven't seen a pointer, we won't see one.
3714 if (numNormalPointers == 0)
3715 return PointerDeclaratorKind::NonPointer;
3716
3717 if (auto recordType = type->getAs<RecordType>()) {
3718 RecordDecl *recordDecl = recordType->getDecl();
3719
3720 bool isCFError = false;
3721 if (S.CFError) {
3722 // If we already know about CFError, test it directly.
3723 isCFError = (S.CFError == recordDecl);
3724 } else {
3725 // Check whether this is CFError, which we identify based on its bridge
3726 // to NSError. CFErrorRef used to be declared with "objc_bridge" but is
3727 // now declared with "objc_bridge_mutable", so look for either one of
3728 // the two attributes.
3729 if (recordDecl->getTagKind() == TTK_Struct && numNormalPointers > 0) {
3730 IdentifierInfo *bridgedType = nullptr;
3731 if (auto bridgeAttr = recordDecl->getAttr<ObjCBridgeAttr>())
3732 bridgedType = bridgeAttr->getBridgedType();
3733 else if (auto bridgeAttr =
3734 recordDecl->getAttr<ObjCBridgeMutableAttr>())
3735 bridgedType = bridgeAttr->getBridgedType();
3736
3737 if (bridgedType == S.getNSErrorIdent()) {
3738 S.CFError = recordDecl;
3739 isCFError = true;
3740 }
3741 }
3742 }
3743
3744 // If this is CFErrorRef*, report it as such.
3745 if (isCFError && numNormalPointers == 2 && numTypeSpecifierPointers < 2) {
3746 return PointerDeclaratorKind::CFErrorRefPointer;
3747 }
3748 break;
3749 }
3750
3751 break;
3752 } while (true);
3753
3754 switch (numNormalPointers) {
3755 case 0:
3756 return PointerDeclaratorKind::NonPointer;
3757
3758 case 1:
3759 return PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer;
3760
3761 case 2:
3762 return PointerDeclaratorKind::MaybePointerToCFRef;
3763
3764 default:
3765 return PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer;
3766 }
3767}
3768
3769static FileID getNullabilityCompletenessCheckFileID(Sema &S,
3770 SourceLocation loc) {
3771 // If we're anywhere in a function, method, or closure context, don't perform
3772 // completeness checks.
3773 for (DeclContext *ctx = S.CurContext; ctx; ctx = ctx->getParent()) {
3774 if (ctx->isFunctionOrMethod())
3775 return FileID();
3776
3777 if (ctx->isFileContext())
3778 break;
3779 }
3780
3781 // We only care about the expansion location.
3782 loc = S.SourceMgr.getExpansionLoc(loc);
3783 FileID file = S.SourceMgr.getFileID(loc);
3784 if (file.isInvalid())
3785 return FileID();
3786
3787 // Retrieve file information.
3788 bool invalid = false;
3789 const SrcMgr::SLocEntry &sloc = S.SourceMgr.getSLocEntry(file, &invalid);
3790 if (invalid || !sloc.isFile())
3791 return FileID();
3792
3793 // We don't want to perform completeness checks on the main file or in
3794 // system headers.
3795 const SrcMgr::FileInfo &fileInfo = sloc.getFile();
3796 if (fileInfo.getIncludeLoc().isInvalid())
3797 return FileID();
3798 if (fileInfo.getFileCharacteristic() != SrcMgr::C_User &&
3799 S.Diags.getSuppressSystemWarnings()) {
3800 return FileID();
3801 }
3802
3803 return file;
3804}
3805
3806/// Creates a fix-it to insert a C-style nullability keyword at \p pointerLoc,
3807/// taking into account whitespace before and after.
3808static void fixItNullability(Sema &S, DiagnosticBuilder &Diag,
3809 SourceLocation PointerLoc,
3810 NullabilityKind Nullability) {
3811 assert(PointerLoc.isValid());
3812 if (PointerLoc.isMacroID())
3813 return;
3814
3815 SourceLocation FixItLoc = S.getLocForEndOfToken(PointerLoc);
3816 if (!FixItLoc.isValid() || FixItLoc == PointerLoc)
3817 return;
3818
3819 const char *NextChar = S.SourceMgr.getCharacterData(FixItLoc);
3820 if (!NextChar)
3821 return;
3822
3823 SmallString<32> InsertionTextBuf{" "};
3824 InsertionTextBuf += getNullabilitySpelling(Nullability);
3825 InsertionTextBuf += " ";
3826 StringRef InsertionText = InsertionTextBuf.str();
3827
3828 if (isWhitespace(*NextChar)) {
3829 InsertionText = InsertionText.drop_back();
3830 } else if (NextChar[-1] == '[') {
3831 if (NextChar[0] == ']')
3832 InsertionText = InsertionText.drop_back().drop_front();
3833 else
3834 InsertionText = InsertionText.drop_front();
3835 } else if (!isIdentifierBody(NextChar[0], /*allow dollar*/true) &&
3836 !isIdentifierBody(NextChar[-1], /*allow dollar*/true)) {
3837 InsertionText = InsertionText.drop_back().drop_front();
3838 }
3839
3840 Diag << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(FixItLoc, InsertionText);
3841}
3842
3843static void emitNullabilityConsistencyWarning(Sema &S,
3844 SimplePointerKind PointerKind,
3845 SourceLocation PointerLoc,
3846 SourceLocation PointerEndLoc) {
3847 assert(PointerLoc.isValid());
3848
3849 if (PointerKind == SimplePointerKind::Array) {
3850 S.Diag(PointerLoc, diag::warn_nullability_missing_array);
3851 } else {
3852 S.Diag(PointerLoc, diag::warn_nullability_missing)
3853 << static_cast<unsigned>(PointerKind);
3854 }
3855
3856 auto FixItLoc = PointerEndLoc.isValid() ? PointerEndLoc : PointerLoc;
3857 if (FixItLoc.isMacroID())
3858 return;
3859
3860 auto addFixIt = [&](NullabilityKind Nullability) {
3861 auto Diag = S.Diag(FixItLoc, diag::note_nullability_fix_it);
3862 Diag << static_cast<unsigned>(Nullability);
3863 Diag << static_cast<unsigned>(PointerKind);
3864 fixItNullability(S, Diag, FixItLoc, Nullability);
3865 };
3866 addFixIt(NullabilityKind::Nullable);
3867 addFixIt(NullabilityKind::NonNull);
3868}
3869
3870/// Complains about missing nullability if the file containing \p pointerLoc
3871/// has other uses of nullability (either the keywords or the \c assume_nonnull
3872/// pragma).
3873///
3874/// If the file has \e not seen other uses of nullability, this particular
3875/// pointer is saved for possible later diagnosis. See recordNullabilitySeen().
3876static void
3877checkNullabilityConsistency(Sema &S, SimplePointerKind pointerKind,
3878 SourceLocation pointerLoc,
3879 SourceLocation pointerEndLoc = SourceLocation()) {
3880 // Determine which file we're performing consistency checking for.
3881 FileID file = getNullabilityCompletenessCheckFileID(S, pointerLoc);
3882 if (file.isInvalid())
3883 return;
3884
3885 // If we haven't seen any type nullability in this file, we won't warn now
3886 // about anything.
3887 FileNullability &fileNullability = S.NullabilityMap[file];
3888 if (!fileNullability.SawTypeNullability) {
3889 // If this is the first pointer declarator in the file, and the appropriate
3890 // warning is on, record it in case we need to diagnose it retroactively.
3891 diag::kind diagKind;
3892 if (pointerKind == SimplePointerKind::Array)
3893 diagKind = diag::warn_nullability_missing_array;
3894 else
3895 diagKind = diag::warn_nullability_missing;
3896
3897 if (fileNullability.PointerLoc.isInvalid() &&
3898 !S.Context.getDiagnostics().isIgnored(diagKind, pointerLoc)) {
3899 fileNullability.PointerLoc = pointerLoc;
3900 fileNullability.PointerEndLoc = pointerEndLoc;
3901 fileNullability.PointerKind = static_cast<unsigned>(pointerKind);
3902 }
3903
3904 return;
3905 }
3906
3907 // Complain about missing nullability.
3908 emitNullabilityConsistencyWarning(S, pointerKind, pointerLoc, pointerEndLoc);
3909}
3910
3911/// Marks that a nullability feature has been used in the file containing
3912/// \p loc.
3913///
3914/// If this file already had pointer types in it that were missing nullability,
3915/// the first such instance is retroactively diagnosed.
3916///
3917/// \sa checkNullabilityConsistency
3918static void recordNullabilitySeen(Sema &S, SourceLocation loc) {
3919 FileID file = getNullabilityCompletenessCheckFileID(S, loc);
3920 if (file.isInvalid())
3921 return;
3922
3923 FileNullability &fileNullability = S.NullabilityMap[file];
3924 if (fileNullability.SawTypeNullability)
3925 return;
3926 fileNullability.SawTypeNullability = true;
3927
3928 // If we haven't seen any type nullability before, now we have. Retroactively
3929 // diagnose the first unannotated pointer, if there was one.
3930 if (fileNullability.PointerLoc.isInvalid())
3931 return;
3932
3933 auto kind = static_cast<SimplePointerKind>(fileNullability.PointerKind);
3934 emitNullabilityConsistencyWarning(S, kind, fileNullability.PointerLoc,
3935 fileNullability.PointerEndLoc);
3936}
3937
3938/// Returns true if any of the declarator chunks before \p endIndex include a
3939/// level of indirection: array, pointer, reference, or pointer-to-member.
3940///
3941/// Because declarator chunks are stored in outer-to-inner order, testing
3942/// every chunk before \p endIndex is testing all chunks that embed the current
3943/// chunk as part of their type.
3944///
3945/// It is legal to pass the result of Declarator::getNumTypeObjects() as the
3946/// end index, in which case all chunks are tested.
3947static bool hasOuterPointerLikeChunk(const Declarator &D, unsigned endIndex) {
3948 unsigned i = endIndex;
3949 while (i != 0) {
3950 // Walk outwards along the declarator chunks.
3951 --i;
3952 const DeclaratorChunk &DC = D.getTypeObject(i);
3953 switch (DC.Kind) {
3954 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
3955 break;
3956 case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
3957 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
3958 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
3959 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
3960 return true;
3961 case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
3962 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
3963 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
3964 // These are invalid anyway, so just ignore.
3965 break;
3966 }
3967 }
3968 return false;
3969}
3970
3971static bool IsNoDerefableChunk(DeclaratorChunk Chunk) {
3972 return (Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pointer ||
3973 Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Array);
3974}
3975
3976template<typename AttrT>
3977static AttrT *createSimpleAttr(ASTContext &Ctx, ParsedAttr &Attr) {
3978 Attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
3979 return ::new (Ctx)
3980 AttrT(Attr.getRange(), Ctx, Attr.getAttributeSpellingListIndex());
3981}
3982
3983static Attr *createNullabilityAttr(ASTContext &Ctx, ParsedAttr &Attr,
3984 NullabilityKind NK) {
3985 switch (NK) {
3986 case NullabilityKind::NonNull:
3987 return createSimpleAttr<TypeNonNullAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
3988
3989 case NullabilityKind::Nullable:
3990 return createSimpleAttr<TypeNullableAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
3991
3992 case NullabilityKind::Unspecified:
3993 return createSimpleAttr<TypeNullUnspecifiedAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
3994 }
3995 llvm_unreachable("unknown NullabilityKind");
3996}
3997
3998// Diagnose whether this is a case with the multiple addr spaces.
3999// Returns true if this is an invalid case.
4000// ISO/IEC TR 18037 S5.3 (amending C99 6.7.3): "No type shall be qualified
4001// by qualifiers for two or more different address spaces."
4002static bool DiagnoseMultipleAddrSpaceAttributes(Sema &S, LangAS ASOld,
4003 LangAS ASNew,
4004 SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
4005 if (ASOld != LangAS::Default) {
4006 if (ASOld != ASNew) {
4007 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_address_multiple_qualifiers);
4008 return true;
4009 }
4010 // Emit a warning if they are identical; it's likely unintended.
4011 S.Diag(AttrLoc,
4012 diag::warn_attribute_address_multiple_identical_qualifiers);
4013 }
4014 return false;
4015}
4016
4017static TypeSourceInfo *
4018GetTypeSourceInfoForDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &State,
4019 QualType T, TypeSourceInfo *ReturnTypeInfo);
4020
4021static TypeSourceInfo *GetFullTypeForDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &state,
4022 QualType declSpecType,
4023 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo) {
4024 // The TypeSourceInfo that this function returns will not be a null type.
4025 // If there is an error, this function will fill in a dummy type as fallback.
4026 QualType T = declSpecType;
4027 Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
4028 Sema &S = state.getSema();
4029 ASTContext &Context = S.Context;
4030 const LangOptions &LangOpts = S.getLangOpts();
4031 bool IsIntegerPointerInPureCapABI = false;
4032
4033 // The name we're declaring, if any.
4034 DeclarationName Name;
4035 if (D.getIdentifier())
4036 Name = D.getIdentifier();
4037
4038 // Does this declaration declare a typedef-name?
4039 bool IsTypedefName =
4040 D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::SCS_typedef ||
4041 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasDeclContext ||
4042 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplateContext;
4043
4044 // Does T refer to a function type with a cv-qualifier or a ref-qualifier?
4045 bool IsQualifiedFunction = T->isFunctionProtoType() &&
4046 (!T->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getMethodQuals().empty() ||
4047 T->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getRefQualifier() != RQ_None);
4048
4049 // If T is 'decltype(auto)', the only declarators we can have are parens
4050 // and at most one function declarator if this is a function declaration.
4051 // If T is a deduced class template specialization type, we can have no
4052 // declarator chunks at all.
4053 if (auto *DT = T->getAs<DeducedType>()) {
4054 const AutoType *AT = T->getAs<AutoType>();
4055 bool IsClassTemplateDeduction = isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(DT);
4056 if ((AT && AT->isDecltypeAuto()) || IsClassTemplateDeduction) {
4057 for (unsigned I = 0, E = D.getNumTypeObjects(); I != E; ++I) {
4058 unsigned Index = E - I - 1;
4059 DeclaratorChunk &DeclChunk = D.getTypeObject(Index);
4060 unsigned DiagId = IsClassTemplateDeduction
4061 ? diag::err_deduced_class_template_compound_type
4062 : diag::err_decltype_auto_compound_type;
4063 unsigned DiagKind = 0;
4064 switch (DeclChunk.Kind) {
4065 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
4066 // FIXME: Rejecting this is a little silly.
4067 if (IsClassTemplateDeduction) {
4068 DiagKind = 4;
4069 break;
4070 }
4071 continue;
4072 case DeclaratorChunk::Function: {
4073 if (IsClassTemplateDeduction) {
4074 DiagKind = 3;
4075 break;
4076 }
4077 unsigned FnIndex;
4078 if (D.isFunctionDeclarationContext() &&
4079 D.isFunctionDeclarator(FnIndex) && FnIndex == Index)
4080 continue;
4081 DiagId = diag::err_decltype_auto_function_declarator_not_declaration;
4082 break;
4083 }
4084 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
4085 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
4086 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
4087 DiagKind = 0;
4088 break;
4089 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
4090 DiagKind = 1;
4091 break;
4092 case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
4093 DiagKind = 2;
4094 break;
4095 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
4096 break;
4097 }
4098
4099 S.Diag(DeclChunk.Loc, DiagId) << DiagKind;
4100 D.setInvalidType(true);
4101 break;
4102 }
4103 }
4104 }
4105
4106 // Determine whether we should infer _Nonnull on pointer types.
4107 Optional<NullabilityKind> inferNullability;
4108 bool inferNullabilityCS = false;
4109 bool inferNullabilityInnerOnly = false;
4110 bool inferNullabilityInnerOnlyComplete = false;
4111
4112 // Are we in an assume-nonnull region?
4113 bool inAssumeNonNullRegion = false;
4114 SourceLocation assumeNonNullLoc = S.PP.getPragmaAssumeNonNullLoc();
4115 if (assumeNonNullLoc.isValid()) {
4116 inAssumeNonNullRegion = true;
4117 recordNullabilitySeen(S, assumeNonNullLoc);
4118 }
4119
4120 // Whether to complain about missing nullability specifiers or not.
4121 enum {
4122 /// Never complain.
4123 CAMN_No,
4124 /// Complain on the inner pointers (but not the outermost
4125 /// pointer).
4126 CAMN_InnerPointers,
4127 /// Complain about any pointers that don't have nullability
4128 /// specified or inferred.
4129 CAMN_Yes
4130 } complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_No;
4131 unsigned NumPointersRemaining = 0;
4132 auto complainAboutInferringWithinChunk = PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::None;
4133
4134 if (IsTypedefName) {
4135 // For typedefs, we do not infer any nullability (the default),
4136 // and we only complain about missing nullability specifiers on
4137 // inner pointers.
4138 complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_InnerPointers;
4139
4140 if (T->canHaveNullability(/*ResultIfUnknown*/false) &&
4141 !T->getNullability(S.Context)) {
4142 // Note that we allow but don't require nullability on dependent types.
4143 ++NumPointersRemaining;
4144 }
4145
4146 for (unsigned i = 0, n = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != n; ++i) {
4147 DeclaratorChunk &chunk = D.getTypeObject(i);
4148 switch (chunk.Kind) {
4149 case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
4150 case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
4151 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
4152 break;
4153
4154 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
4155 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
4156 ++NumPointersRemaining;
4157 break;
4158
4159 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
4160 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
4161 continue;
4162
4163 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
4164 ++NumPointersRemaining;
4165 continue;
4166 }
4167 }
4168 } else {
4169 bool isFunctionOrMethod = false;
4170 switch (auto context = state.getDeclarator().getContext()) {
4171 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameterContext:
4172 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCResultContext:
4173 case DeclaratorContext::PrototypeContext:
4174 case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnContext:
4175 case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnVarContext:
4176 isFunctionOrMethod = true;
4177 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4178
4179 case DeclaratorContext::MemberContext:
4180 if (state.getDeclarator().isObjCIvar() && !isFunctionOrMethod) {
4181 complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_No;
4182 break;
4183 }
4184
4185 // Weak properties are inferred to be nullable.
4186 if (state.getDeclarator().isObjCWeakProperty() && inAssumeNonNullRegion) {
4187 inferNullability = NullabilityKind::Nullable;
4188 break;
4189 }
4190
4191 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4192
4193 case DeclaratorContext::FileContext:
4194 case DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeListContext: {
4195 complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_Yes;
4196
4197 // Nullability inference depends on the type and declarator.
4198 auto wrappingKind = PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::None;
4199 switch (classifyPointerDeclarator(S, T, D, wrappingKind)) {
4200 case PointerDeclaratorKind::NonPointer:
4201 case PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer:
4202 // Cannot infer nullability.
4203 break;
4204
4205 case PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer:
4206 // Infer _Nonnull if we are in an assumes-nonnull region.
4207 if (inAssumeNonNullRegion) {
4208 complainAboutInferringWithinChunk = wrappingKind;
4209 inferNullability = NullabilityKind::NonNull;
4210 inferNullabilityCS =
4211 (context == DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameterContext ||
4212 context == DeclaratorContext::ObjCResultContext);
4213 }
4214 break;
4215
4216 case PointerDeclaratorKind::CFErrorRefPointer:
4217 case PointerDeclaratorKind::NSErrorPointerPointer:
4218 // Within a function or method signature, infer _Nullable at both
4219 // levels.
4220 if (isFunctionOrMethod && inAssumeNonNullRegion)
4221 inferNullability = NullabilityKind::Nullable;
4222 break;
4223
4224 case PointerDeclaratorKind::MaybePointerToCFRef:
4225 if (isFunctionOrMethod) {
4226 // On pointer-to-pointer parameters marked cf_returns_retained or
4227 // cf_returns_not_retained, if the outer pointer is explicit then
4228 // infer the inner pointer as _Nullable.
4229 auto hasCFReturnsAttr =
4230 [](const ParsedAttributesView &AttrList) -> bool {
4231 return AttrList.hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained) ||
4232 AttrList.hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained);
4233 };
4234 if (const auto *InnermostChunk = D.getInnermostNonParenChunk()) {
4235 if (hasCFReturnsAttr(D.getAttributes()) ||
4236 hasCFReturnsAttr(InnermostChunk->getAttrs()) ||
4237 hasCFReturnsAttr(D.getDeclSpec().getAttributes())) {
4238 inferNullability = NullabilityKind::Nullable;
4239 inferNullabilityInnerOnly = true;
4240 }
4241 }
4242 }
4243 break;
4244 }
4245 break;
4246 }
4247
4248 case DeclaratorContext::ConversionIdContext:
4249 complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_Yes;
4250 break;
4251
4252 case DeclaratorContext::AliasDeclContext:
4253 case DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplateContext:
4254 case DeclaratorContext::BlockContext:
4255 case DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteralContext:
4256 case DeclaratorContext::ConditionContext:
4257 case DeclaratorContext::CXXCatchContext:
4258 case DeclaratorContext::CXXNewContext:
4259 case DeclaratorContext::ForContext:
4260 case DeclaratorContext::InitStmtContext:
4261 case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprContext:
4262 case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameterContext:
4263 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCCatchContext:
4264 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateParamContext:
4265 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateArgContext:
4266 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArgContext:
4267 case DeclaratorContext::TypeNameContext:
4268 case DeclaratorContext::FunctionalCastContext:
4269 // Don't infer in these contexts.
4270 break;
4271 }
4272 }
4273
4274 // Local function that returns true if its argument looks like a va_list.
4275 auto isVaList = [&S](QualType T) -> bool {
4276 auto *typedefTy = T->getAs<TypedefType>();
4277 if (!typedefTy)
4278 return false;
4279 TypedefDecl *vaListTypedef = S.Context.getBuiltinVaListDecl();
4280 do {
4281 if (typedefTy->getDecl() == vaListTypedef)
4282 return true;
4283 if (auto *name = typedefTy->getDecl()->getIdentifier())
4284 if (name->isStr("va_list"))
4285 return true;
4286 typedefTy = typedefTy->desugar()->getAs<TypedefType>();
4287 } while (typedefTy);
4288 return false;
4289 };
4290
4291 // Local function that checks the nullability for a given pointer declarator.
4292 // Returns true if _Nonnull was inferred.
4293 auto inferPointerNullability =
4294 [&](SimplePointerKind pointerKind, SourceLocation pointerLoc,
4295 SourceLocation pointerEndLoc,
4296 ParsedAttributesView &attrs, AttributePool &Pool) -> ParsedAttr * {
4297 // We've seen a pointer.
4298 if (NumPointersRemaining > 0)
4299 --NumPointersRemaining;
4300
4301 // If a nullability attribute is present, there's nothing to do.
4302 if (hasNullabilityAttr(attrs))
4303 return nullptr;
4304
4305 // If we're supposed to infer nullability, do so now.
4306 if (inferNullability && !inferNullabilityInnerOnlyComplete) {
4307 ParsedAttr::Syntax syntax = inferNullabilityCS
4308 ? ParsedAttr::AS_ContextSensitiveKeyword
4309 : ParsedAttr::AS_Keyword;
4310 ParsedAttr *nullabilityAttr = Pool.create(
4311 S.getNullabilityKeyword(*inferNullability), SourceRange(pointerLoc),
4312 nullptr, SourceLocation(), nullptr, 0, syntax);
4313
4314 attrs.addAtEnd(nullabilityAttr);
4315
4316 if (inferNullabilityCS) {
4317 state.getDeclarator().getMutableDeclSpec().getObjCQualifiers()
4318 ->setObjCDeclQualifier(ObjCDeclSpec::DQ_CSNullability);
4319 }
4320
4321 if (pointerLoc.isValid() &&
4322 complainAboutInferringWithinChunk !=
4323 PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::None) {
4324 auto Diag =
4325 S.Diag(pointerLoc, diag::warn_nullability_inferred_on_nested_type);
4326 Diag << static_cast<int>(complainAboutInferringWithinChunk);
4327 fixItNullability(S, Diag, pointerLoc, NullabilityKind::NonNull);
4328 }
4329
4330 if (inferNullabilityInnerOnly)
4331 inferNullabilityInnerOnlyComplete = true;
4332 return nullabilityAttr;
4333 }
4334
4335 // If we're supposed to complain about missing nullability, do so
4336 // now if it's truly missing.
4337 switch (complainAboutMissingNullability) {
4338 case CAMN_No:
4339 break;
4340
4341 case CAMN_InnerPointers:
4342 if (NumPointersRemaining == 0)
4343 break;
4344 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4345
4346 case CAMN_Yes:
4347 checkNullabilityConsistency(S, pointerKind, pointerLoc, pointerEndLoc);
4348 }
4349 return nullptr;
4350 };
4351
4352 // If the type itself could have nullability but does not, infer pointer
4353 // nullability and perform consistency checking.
4354 if (S.CodeSynthesisContexts.empty()) {
4355 if (T->canHaveNullability(/*ResultIfUnknown*/false) &&
4356 !T->getNullability(S.Context)) {
4357 if (isVaList(T)) {
4358 // Record that we've seen a pointer, but do nothing else.
4359 if (NumPointersRemaining > 0)
4360 --NumPointersRemaining;
4361 } else {
4362 SimplePointerKind pointerKind = SimplePointerKind::Pointer;
4363 if (T->isBlockPointerType())
4364 pointerKind = SimplePointerKind::BlockPointer;
4365 else if (T->isMemberPointerType())
4366 pointerKind = SimplePointerKind::MemberPointer;
4367
4368 if (auto *attr = inferPointerNullability(
4369 pointerKind, D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
4370 D.getDeclSpec().getEndLoc(),
4371 D.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes(),
4372 D.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributePool())) {
4373 T = state.getAttributedType(
4374 createNullabilityAttr(Context, *attr, *inferNullability), T, T);
4375 }
4376 }
4377 }
4378
4379 if (complainAboutMissingNullability == CAMN_Yes &&
4380 T->isArrayType() && !T->getNullability(S.Context) && !isVaList(T) &&
4381 D.isPrototypeContext() &&
4382 !hasOuterPointerLikeChunk(D, D.getNumTypeObjects())) {
4383 checkNullabilityConsistency(S, SimplePointerKind::Array,
4384 D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
4385 }
4386 }
4387
4388 bool ExpectNoDerefChunk =
4389 state.getCurrentAttributes().hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_NoDeref);
4390
4391 // Walk the DeclTypeInfo, building the recursive type as we go.
4392 // DeclTypeInfos are ordered from the identifier out, which is
4393 // opposite of what we want :).
4394 for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
4395 unsigned chunkIndex = e - i - 1;
4396 state.setCurrentChunkIndex(chunkIndex);
4397 DeclaratorChunk &DeclType = D.getTypeObject(chunkIndex);
