4398 IsQualifiedFunction &= DeclType.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Paren;
4399 switch (DeclType.Kind) {
4400 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
4401 if (i == 0)
4402 warnAboutRedundantParens(S, D, T);
4403 T = S.BuildParenType(T);
4404 break;
4405 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
4406 // If blocks are disabled, emit an error.
4407 if (!LangOpts.Blocks)
4408 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_blocks_disable) << LangOpts.OpenCL;
4409
4410 // Handle pointer nullability.
4411 inferPointerNullability(SimplePointerKind::BlockPointer, DeclType.Loc,
4412 DeclType.EndLoc, DeclType.getAttrs(),
4413 state.getDeclarator().getAttributePool());
4414
4415 T = S.BuildBlockPointerType(T, D.getIdentifierLoc(), Name);
4416 if (DeclType.Cls.TypeQuals || LangOpts.OpenCL) {
4417 // OpenCL v2.0, s6.12.5 - Block variable declarations are implicitly
4418 // qualified with const.
4419 if (LangOpts.OpenCL)
4420 DeclType.Cls.TypeQuals |= DeclSpec::TQ_const;
4421 T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, DeclType.Cls.TypeQuals);
4422 }
4423 break;
4424 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer: {
4425 // Verify that we're not building a pointer to pointer to function with
4426 // exception specification.
4427 if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && S.CheckDistantExceptionSpec(T)) {
4428 S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_distant_exception_spec);
4429 D.setInvalidType(true);
4430 // Build the type anyway.
4431 }
4432
4433 // Handle pointer nullability
4434 inferPointerNullability(SimplePointerKind::Pointer, DeclType.Loc,
4435 DeclType.EndLoc, DeclType.getAttrs(),
4436 state.getDeclarator().getAttributePool());
4437
4438 if (LangOpts.ObjC && T->getAs<ObjCObjectType>()) {
4439 T = Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(T);
4440 if (DeclType.Ptr.TypeQuals)
4441 T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, DeclType.Ptr.TypeQuals);
4442 break;
4443 }
4444
4445 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.9b - Pointer to image/sampler cannot be used.
4446 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.13.16.1 - Pointer to pipe cannot be used.
4447 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.12.5 - Pointers to Blocks are not allowed.
4448 if (LangOpts.OpenCL) {
4449 if (T->isImageType() || T->isSamplerT() || T->isPipeType() ||
4450 T->isBlockPointerType()) {
4451 S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_opencl_pointer_to_type) << T;
4452 D.setInvalidType(true);
4453 }
4454 }
4455 bool ValidPointer = false;
4456 T = S.BuildPointerType(T, DeclType.Loc, Name, &ValidPointer);
4457 if (!ValidPointer) {
4458 IsIntegerPointerInPureCapABI = true; // FIXME: is this correct?
4459 } else if (DeclType.Ptr.TypeQuals)
4460 T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, DeclType.Ptr.TypeQuals);
4461 break;
4462 }
4463 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference: {
4464 // Verify that we're not building a reference to pointer to function with
4465 // exception specification.
4466 if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && S.CheckDistantExceptionSpec(T)) {
4467 S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_distant_exception_spec);
4468 D.setInvalidType(true);
4469 // Build the type anyway.
4470 }
4471 T = S.BuildReferenceType(T, DeclType.Ref.LValueRef, DeclType.Loc, Name);
4472
4473 if (DeclType.Ref.HasRestrict)
4474 T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, Qualifiers::Restrict);
4475 break;
4476 }
4477 case DeclaratorChunk::Array: {
4478 // Verify that we're not building an array of pointers to function with
4479 // exception specification.
4480 if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && S.CheckDistantExceptionSpec(T)) {
4481 S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_distant_exception_spec);
4482 D.setInvalidType(true);
4483 // Build the type anyway.
4484 }
4485 DeclaratorChunk::ArrayTypeInfo &ATI = DeclType.Arr;
4486 Expr *ArraySize = static_cast<Expr*>(ATI.NumElts);
4487 ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM;
4488 if (ATI.isStar)
4489 ASM = ArrayType::Star;
4490 else if (ATI.hasStatic)
4491 ASM = ArrayType::Static;
4492 else
4493 ASM = ArrayType::Normal;
4494 if (ASM == ArrayType::Star && !D.isPrototypeContext()) {
4495 // FIXME: This check isn't quite right: it allows star in prototypes
4496 // for function definitions, and disallows some edge cases detailed
4497 // in http://gcc.gnu.org/ml/gcc-patches/2009-02/msg00133.html
4498 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_array_star_outside_prototype);
4499 ASM = ArrayType::Normal;
4500 D.setInvalidType(true);
4501 }
4502
4503 // C99 6.7.5.2p1: The optional type qualifiers and the keyword static
4504 // shall appear only in a declaration of a function parameter with an
4505 // array type, ...
4506 if (ASM == ArrayType::Static || ATI.TypeQuals) {
4507 if (!(D.isPrototypeContext() ||
4508 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeListContext)) {
4509 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_array_static_outside_prototype) <<
4510 (ASM == ArrayType::Static ? "'static'" : "type qualifier");
4511 // Remove the 'static' and the type qualifiers.
4512 if (ASM == ArrayType::Static)
4513 ASM = ArrayType::Normal;
4514 ATI.TypeQuals = 0;
4515 D.setInvalidType(true);
4516 }
4517
4518 // C99 6.7.5.2p1: ... and then only in the outermost array type
4519 // derivation.
4520 if (hasOuterPointerLikeChunk(D, chunkIndex)) {
4521 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_array_static_not_outermost) <<
4522 (ASM == ArrayType::Static ? "'static'" : "type qualifier");
4523 if (ASM == ArrayType::Static)
4524 ASM = ArrayType::Normal;
4525 ATI.TypeQuals = 0;
4526 D.setInvalidType(true);
4527 }
4528 }
4529 const AutoType *AT = T->getContainedAutoType();
4530 // Allow arrays of auto if we are a generic lambda parameter.
4531 // i.e. [](auto (&array)[5]) { return array[0]; }; OK
4532 if (AT &&
4533 D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameterContext) {
4534 // We've already diagnosed this for decltype(auto).
4535 if (!AT->isDecltypeAuto())
4536 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_array_of_auto)
4537 << getPrintableNameForEntity(Name) << T;
4538 T = QualType();
4539 break;
4540 }
4541
4542 // Array parameters can be marked nullable as well, although it's not
4543 // necessary if they're marked 'static'.
4544 if (complainAboutMissingNullability == CAMN_Yes &&
4545 !hasNullabilityAttr(DeclType.getAttrs()) &&
4546 ASM != ArrayType::Static &&
4547 D.isPrototypeContext() &&
4548 !hasOuterPointerLikeChunk(D, chunkIndex)) {
4549 checkNullabilityConsistency(S, SimplePointerKind::Array, DeclType.Loc);
4550 }
4551
4552 T = S.BuildArrayType(T, ASM, ArraySize, ATI.TypeQuals,
4553 SourceRange(DeclType.Loc, DeclType.EndLoc), Name);
4554 break;
4555 }
4556 case DeclaratorChunk::Function: {
4557 // If the function declarator has a prototype (i.e. it is not () and
4558 // does not have a K&R-style identifier list), then the arguments are part
4559 // of the type, otherwise the argument list is ().
4560 DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI = DeclType.Fun;
4561 IsQualifiedFunction =
4562 FTI.hasMethodTypeQualifiers() || FTI.hasRefQualifier();
4563
4564 // Check for auto functions and trailing return type and adjust the
4565 // return type accordingly.
4566 if (!D.isInvalidType()) {
4567 // trailing-return-type is only required if we're declaring a function,
4568 // and not, for instance, a pointer to a function.
4569 if (D.getDeclSpec().hasAutoTypeSpec() &&
4570 !FTI.hasTrailingReturnType() && chunkIndex == 0) {
4571 if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14) {
4572 S.Diag(D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
4573 D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_auto
4574 ? diag::err_auto_missing_trailing_return
4575 : diag::err_deduced_return_type);
4576 T = Context.IntTy;
4577 D.setInvalidType(true);
4578 } else {
4579 S.Diag(D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
4580 diag::warn_cxx11_compat_deduced_return_type);
4581 }
4582 } else if (FTI.hasTrailingReturnType()) {
4583 // T must be exactly 'auto' at this point. See CWG issue 681.
4584 if (isa<ParenType>(T)) {
4585 S.Diag(D.getBeginLoc(), diag::err_trailing_return_in_parens)
4586 << T << D.getSourceRange();
4587 D.setInvalidType(true);
4588 } else if (D.getName().getKind() ==
4589 UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_DeductionGuideName) {
4590 if (T != Context.DependentTy) {
4591 S.Diag(D.getDeclSpec().getBeginLoc(),
4592 diag::err_deduction_guide_with_complex_decl)
4593 << D.getSourceRange();
4594 D.setInvalidType(true);
4595 }
4596 } else if (D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprContext &&
4597 (T.hasQualifiers() || !isa<AutoType>(T) ||
4598 cast<AutoType>(T)->getKeyword() !=
4599 AutoTypeKeyword::Auto)) {
4600 S.Diag(D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
4601 diag::err_trailing_return_without_auto)
4602 << T << D.getDeclSpec().getSourceRange();
4603 D.setInvalidType(true);
4604 }
4605 T = S.GetTypeFromParser(FTI.getTrailingReturnType(), &TInfo);
4606 if (T.isNull()) {
4607 // An error occurred parsing the trailing return type.
4608 T = Context.IntTy;
4609 D.setInvalidType(true);
4610 }
4611 } else {
4612 // This function type is not the type of the entity being declared,
4613 // so checking the 'auto' is not the responsibility of this chunk.
4614 }
4615 }
4616
4617 // C99 6.7.5.3p1: The return type may not be a function or array type.
4618 // For conversion functions, we'll diagnose this particular error later.
4619 if (!D.isInvalidType() && (T->isArrayType() || T->isFunctionType()) &&
4620 (D.getName().getKind() !=
4621 UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConversionFunctionId)) {
4622 unsigned diagID = diag::err_func_returning_array_function;
4623 // Last processing chunk in block context means this function chunk
4624 // represents the block.
4625 if (chunkIndex == 0 &&
4626 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteralContext)
4627 diagID = diag::err_block_returning_array_function;
4628 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diagID) << T->isFunctionType() << T;
4629 T = Context.IntTy;
4630 D.setInvalidType(true);
4631 }
4632
4633 // Do not allow returning half FP value.
4634 // FIXME: This really should be in BuildFunctionType.
4635 if (T->isHalfType()) {
4636 if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
4637 if (!S.getOpenCLOptions().isEnabled("cl_khr_fp16")) {
4638 S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_opencl_invalid_return)
4639 << T << 0 /*pointer hint*/;
4640 D.setInvalidType(true);
4641 }
4642 } else if (!S.getLangOpts().HalfArgsAndReturns) {
4643 S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(),
4644 diag::err_parameters_retval_cannot_have_fp16_type) << 1;
4645 D.setInvalidType(true);
4646 }
4647 }
4648
4649 if (LangOpts.OpenCL) {
4650 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.12.5 - A block cannot be the return value of a
4651 // function.
4652 if (T->isBlockPointerType() || T->isImageType() || T->isSamplerT() ||
4653 T->isPipeType()) {
4654 S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_opencl_invalid_return)
4655 << T << 1 /*hint off*/;
4656 D.setInvalidType(true);
4657 }
4658 // OpenCL doesn't support variadic functions and blocks
4659 // (s6.9.e and s6.12.5 OpenCL v2.0) except for printf.
4660 // We also allow here any toolchain reserved identifiers.
4661 if (FTI.isVariadic &&
4662 !(D.getIdentifier() &&
4663 ((D.getIdentifier()->getName() == "printf" &&
4664 (LangOpts.OpenCLCPlusPlus || LangOpts.OpenCLVersion >= 120)) ||
4665 D.getIdentifier()->getName().startswith("__")))) {
4666 S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_opencl_variadic_function);
4667 D.setInvalidType(true);
4668 }
4669 }
4670
4671 // Methods cannot return interface types. All ObjC objects are
4672 // passed by reference.
4673 if (T->isObjCObjectType()) {
4674 SourceLocation DiagLoc, FixitLoc;
4675 if (TInfo) {
4676 DiagLoc = TInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
4677 FixitLoc = S.getLocForEndOfToken(TInfo->getTypeLoc().getEndLoc());
4678 } else {
4679 DiagLoc = D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc();
4680 FixitLoc = S.getLocForEndOfToken(D.getDeclSpec().getEndLoc());
4681 }
4682 S.Diag(DiagLoc, diag::err_object_cannot_be_passed_returned_by_value)
4683 << 0 << T
4684 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(FixitLoc, "*");
4685
4686 T = Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(T);
4687 if (TInfo) {
4688 TypeLocBuilder TLB;
4689 TLB.pushFullCopy(TInfo->getTypeLoc());
4690 ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc TLoc = TLB.push<ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc>(T);
4691 TLoc.setStarLoc(FixitLoc);
4692 TInfo = TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(Context, T);
4693 }
4694
4695 D.setInvalidType(true);
4696 }
4697
4698 // cv-qualifiers on return types are pointless except when the type is a
4699 // class type in C++.
4700 if ((T.getCVRQualifiers() || T->isAtomicType()) &&
4701 !(S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
4702 (T->isDependentType() || T->isRecordType()))) {
4703 if (T->isVoidType() && !S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
4704 D.getFunctionDefinitionKind() == FDK_Definition) {
4705 // [6.9.1/3] qualified void return is invalid on a C
4706 // function definition. Apparently ok on declarations and
4707 // in C++ though (!)
4708 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_func_returning_qualified_void) << T;
4709 } else
4710 diagnoseRedundantReturnTypeQualifiers(S, T, D, chunkIndex);
4711 }
4712
4713 // Objective-C ARC ownership qualifiers are ignored on the function
4714 // return type (by type canonicalization). Complain if this attribute
4715 // was written here.
4716 if (T.getQualifiers().hasObjCLifetime()) {
4717 SourceLocation AttrLoc;
4718 if (chunkIndex + 1 < D.getNumTypeObjects()) {
4719 DeclaratorChunk ReturnTypeChunk = D.getTypeObject(chunkIndex + 1);
4720 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : ReturnTypeChunk.getAttrs()) {
4721 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership) {
4722 AttrLoc = AL.getLoc();
4723 break;
4724 }
4725 }
4726 }
4727 if (AttrLoc.isInvalid()) {
4728 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : D.getDeclSpec().getAttributes()) {
4729 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership) {
4730 AttrLoc = AL.getLoc();
4731 break;
4732 }
4733 }
4734 }
4735
4736 if (AttrLoc.isValid()) {
4737 // The ownership attributes are almost always written via
4738 // the predefined
4739 // __strong/__weak/__autoreleasing/__unsafe_unretained.
4740 if (AttrLoc.isMacroID())
4741 AttrLoc =
4742 S.SourceMgr.getImmediateExpansionRange(AttrLoc).getBegin();
4743
4744 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_arc_lifetime_result_type)
4745 << T.getQualifiers().getObjCLifetime();
4746 }
4747 }
4748
4749 if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && D.getDeclSpec().hasTagDefinition()) {
4750 // C++ [dcl.fct]p6:
4751 // Types shall not be defined in return or parameter types.
4752 TagDecl *Tag = cast<TagDecl>(D.getDeclSpec().getRepAsDecl());
4753 S.Diag(Tag->getLocation(), diag::err_type_defined_in_result_type)
4754 << Context.getTypeDeclType(Tag);
4755 }
4756
4757 // Exception specs are not allowed in typedefs. Complain, but add it
4758 // anyway.
4759 if (IsTypedefName && FTI.getExceptionSpecType() && !LangOpts.CPlusPlus17)
4760 S.Diag(FTI.getExceptionSpecLocBeg(),
4761 diag::err_exception_spec_in_typedef)
4762 << (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasDeclContext ||
4763 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplateContext);
4764
4765 // If we see "T var();" or "T var(T());" at block scope, it is probably
4766 // an attempt to initialize a variable, not a function declaration.
4767 if (FTI.isAmbiguous)
4768 warnAboutAmbiguousFunction(S, D, DeclType, T);
4769
4770 FunctionType::ExtInfo EI(
4771 getCCForDeclaratorChunk(S, D, DeclType.getAttrs(), FTI, chunkIndex));
4772
4773 if (!FTI.NumParams && !FTI.isVariadic && !LangOpts.CPlusPlus
4774 && !LangOpts.OpenCL) {
4775 // Simple void foo(), where the incoming T is the result type.
4776 T = Context.getFunctionNoProtoType(T, EI);
4777 } else {
4778 // We allow a zero-parameter variadic function in C if the
4779 // function is marked with the "overloadable" attribute. Scan
4780 // for this attribute now.
4781 if (!FTI.NumParams && FTI.isVariadic && !LangOpts.CPlusPlus)
4782 if (!D.getAttributes().hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_Overloadable))
4783 S.Diag(FTI.getEllipsisLoc(), diag::err_ellipsis_first_param);
4784
4785 if (FTI.NumParams && FTI.Params[0].Param == nullptr) {
4786 // C99 6.7.5.3p3: Reject int(x,y,z) when it's not a function
4787 // definition.
4788 S.Diag(FTI.Params[0].IdentLoc,
4789 diag::err_ident_list_in_fn_declaration);
4790 D.setInvalidType(true);
4791 // Recover by creating a K&R-style function type.
4792 T = Context.getFunctionNoProtoType(T, EI);
4793 break;
4794 }
4795
4796 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI;
4797 EPI.ExtInfo = EI;
4798 EPI.Variadic = FTI.isVariadic;
4799 EPI.HasTrailingReturn = FTI.hasTrailingReturnType();
4800 EPI.TypeQuals.addCVRUQualifiers(
4801 FTI.MethodQualifiers ? FTI.MethodQualifiers->getTypeQualifiers()
4802 : 0);
4803 EPI.RefQualifier = !FTI.hasRefQualifier()? RQ_None
4804 : FTI.RefQualifierIsLValueRef? RQ_LValue
4805 : RQ_RValue;
4806
4807 // Otherwise, we have a function with a parameter list that is
4808 // potentially variadic.
4809 SmallVector<QualType, 16> ParamTys;
4810 ParamTys.reserve(FTI.NumParams);
4811
4812 SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 16>
4813 ExtParameterInfos(FTI.NumParams);
4814 bool HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = false;
4815
4816 for (unsigned i = 0, e = FTI.NumParams; i != e; ++i) {
4817 ParmVarDecl *Param = cast<ParmVarDecl>(FTI.Params[i].Param);
4818 QualType ParamTy = Param->getType();
4819 assert(!ParamTy.isNull() && "Couldn't parse type?");
4820
4821 // Look for 'void'. void is allowed only as a single parameter to a
4822 // function with no other parameters (C99 6.7.5.3p10). We record
4823 // int(void) as a FunctionProtoType with an empty parameter list.
4824 if (ParamTy->isVoidType()) {
4825 // If this is something like 'float(int, void)', reject it. 'void'
4826 // is an incomplete type (C99 6.2.5p19) and function decls cannot
4827 // have parameters of incomplete type.
4828 if (FTI.NumParams != 1 || FTI.isVariadic) {
4829 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_void_only_param);
4830 ParamTy = Context.IntTy;
4831 Param->setType(ParamTy);
4832 } else if (FTI.Params[i].Ident) {
4833 // Reject, but continue to parse 'int(void abc)'.
4834 S.Diag(FTI.Params[i].IdentLoc, diag::err_param_with_void_type);
4835 ParamTy = Context.IntTy;
4836 Param->setType(ParamTy);
4837 } else {
4838 // Reject, but continue to parse 'float(const void)'.
4839 if (ParamTy.hasQualifiers())
4840 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_void_param_qualified);
4841
4842 // Do not add 'void' to the list.
4843 break;
4844 }
4845 } else if (ParamTy->isHalfType()) {
4846 // Disallow half FP parameters.
4847 // FIXME: This really should be in BuildFunctionType.
4848 if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
4849 if (!S.getOpenCLOptions().isEnabled("cl_khr_fp16")) {
4850 S.Diag(Param->getLocation(),
4851 diag::err_opencl_half_param) << ParamTy;
4852 D.setInvalidType();
4853 Param->setInvalidDecl();
4854 }
4855 } else if (!S.getLangOpts().HalfArgsAndReturns) {
4856 S.Diag(Param->getLocation(),
4857 diag::err_parameters_retval_cannot_have_fp16_type) << 0;
4858 D.setInvalidType();
4859 }
4860 } else if (!FTI.hasPrototype) {
4861 if (ParamTy->isPromotableIntegerType()) {
4862 ParamTy = Context.getPromotedIntegerType(ParamTy);
4863 Param->setKNRPromoted(true);
4864 } else if (const BuiltinType* BTy = ParamTy->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
4865 if (BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::Float) {
4866 ParamTy = Context.DoubleTy;
4867 Param->setKNRPromoted(true);
4868 }
4869 }
4870 }
4871
4872 if (LangOpts.ObjCAutoRefCount && Param->hasAttr<NSConsumedAttr>()) {
4873 ExtParameterInfos[i] = ExtParameterInfos[i].withIsConsumed(true);
4874 HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = true;
4875 }
4876
4877 if (auto attr = Param->getAttr<ParameterABIAttr>()) {
4878 ExtParameterInfos[i] =
4879 ExtParameterInfos[i].withABI(attr->getABI());
4880 HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = true;
4881 }
4882
4883 if (Param->hasAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>()) {
4884 ExtParameterInfos[i] = ExtParameterInfos[i].withHasPassObjectSize();
4885 HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = true;
4886 }
4887
4888 if (Param->hasAttr<NoEscapeAttr>()) {
4889 ExtParameterInfos[i] = ExtParameterInfos[i].withIsNoEscape(true);
4890 HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = true;
4891 }
4892
4893 ParamTys.push_back(ParamTy);
4894 }
4895
4896 if (HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos) {
4897 EPI.ExtParameterInfos = ExtParameterInfos.data();
4898 checkExtParameterInfos(S, ParamTys, EPI,
4899 [&](unsigned i) { return FTI.Params[i].Param->getLocation(); });
4900 }
4901
4902 SmallVector<QualType, 4> Exceptions;
4903 SmallVector<ParsedType, 2> DynamicExceptions;
4904 SmallVector<SourceRange, 2> DynamicExceptionRanges;
4905 Expr *NoexceptExpr = nullptr;
4906
4907 if (FTI.getExceptionSpecType() == EST_Dynamic) {
4908 // FIXME: It's rather inefficient to have to split into two vectors
4909 // here.
4910 unsigned N = FTI.getNumExceptions();
4911 DynamicExceptions.reserve(N);
4912 DynamicExceptionRanges.reserve(N);
4913 for (unsigned I = 0; I != N; ++I) {
4914 DynamicExceptions.push_back(FTI.Exceptions[I].Ty);
4915 DynamicExceptionRanges.push_back(FTI.Exceptions[I].Range);
4916 }
4917 } else if (isComputedNoexcept(FTI.getExceptionSpecType())) {
4918 NoexceptExpr = FTI.NoexceptExpr;
4919 }
4920
4921 S.checkExceptionSpecification(D.isFunctionDeclarationContext(),
4922 FTI.getExceptionSpecType(),
4923 DynamicExceptions,
4924 DynamicExceptionRanges,
4925 NoexceptExpr,
4926 Exceptions,
4927 EPI.ExceptionSpec);
4928
4929 // FIXME: Set address space from attrs for C++ mode here.
4930 // OpenCLCPlusPlus: A class member function has an address space.
4931 auto IsClassMember = [&]() {
4932 return (!state.getDeclarator().getCXXScopeSpec().isEmpty() &&
4933 state.getDeclarator()
4934 .getCXXScopeSpec()
4935 .getScopeRep()
4936 ->getKind() == NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec) ||
4937 state.getDeclarator().getContext() ==
4938 DeclaratorContext::MemberContext;
4939 };
4940
4941 if (state.getSema().getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus && IsClassMember()) {
4942 LangAS ASIdx = LangAS::Default;
4943 // Take address space attr if any and mark as invalid to avoid adding
4944 // them later while creating QualType.
4945 if (FTI.MethodQualifiers)
4946 for (ParsedAttr &attr : FTI.MethodQualifiers->getAttributes()) {
4947 LangAS ASIdxNew = attr.asOpenCLLangAS();
4948 if (DiagnoseMultipleAddrSpaceAttributes(S, ASIdx, ASIdxNew,
4949 attr.getLoc()))
4950 D.setInvalidType(true);
4951 else
4952 ASIdx = ASIdxNew;
4953 }
4954 // If a class member function's address space is not set, set it to
4955 // __generic.
4956 LangAS AS =
4957 (ASIdx == LangAS::Default ? LangAS::opencl_generic : ASIdx);
4958 EPI.TypeQuals.addAddressSpace(AS);
4959 }
4960 T = Context.getFunctionType(T, ParamTys, EPI);
4961 }
4962 break;
4963 }
4964 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer: {
4965 // The scope spec must refer to a class, or be dependent.
4966 CXXScopeSpec &SS = DeclType.Mem.Scope();
4967 QualType ClsType;
4968
4969 // Handle pointer nullability.
4970 inferPointerNullability(SimplePointerKind::MemberPointer, DeclType.Loc,
4971 DeclType.EndLoc, DeclType.getAttrs(),
4972 state.getDeclarator().getAttributePool());
4973
4974 if (SS.isInvalid()) {
4975 // Avoid emitting extra errors if we already errored on the scope.
4976 D.setInvalidType(true);
4977 } else if (S.isDependentScopeSpecifier(SS) ||
4978 dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(S.computeDeclContext(SS))) {
4979 NestedNameSpecifier *NNS = SS.getScopeRep();
4980 NestedNameSpecifier *NNSPrefix = NNS->getPrefix();
4981 switch (NNS->getKind()) {
4982 case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
4983 ClsType = Context.getDependentNameType(ETK_None, NNSPrefix,
4984 NNS->getAsIdentifier());
4985 break;
4986
4987 case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
4988 case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
4989 case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
4990 case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
4991 llvm_unreachable("Nested-name-specifier must name a type");
4992
4993 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
4994 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
4995 ClsType = QualType(NNS->getAsType(), 0);
4996 // Note: if the NNS has a prefix and ClsType is a nondependent
4997 // TemplateSpecializationType, then the NNS prefix is NOT included
4998 // in ClsType; hence we wrap ClsType into an ElaboratedType.
4999 // NOTE: in particular, no wrap occurs if ClsType already is an
5000 // Elaborated, DependentName, or DependentTemplateSpecialization.
5001 if (NNSPrefix && isa<TemplateSpecializationType>(NNS->getAsType()))
5002 ClsType = Context.getElaboratedType(ETK_None, NNSPrefix, ClsType);
5003 break;
5004 }
5005 } else {
5006 S.Diag(DeclType.Mem.Scope().getBeginLoc(),
5007 diag::err_illegal_decl_mempointer_in_nonclass)
5008 << (D.getIdentifier() ? D.getIdentifier()->getName() : "type name")
5009 << DeclType.Mem.Scope().getRange();
5010 D.setInvalidType(true);
5011 }
5012
5013 if (!ClsType.isNull())
5014 T = S.BuildMemberPointerType(T, ClsType, DeclType.Loc,
5015 D.getIdentifier());
5016 if (T.isNull()) {
5017 T = Context.IntTy;
5018 D.setInvalidType(true);
5019 } else if (DeclType.Mem.TypeQuals) {
5020 T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, DeclType.Mem.TypeQuals);
5021 }
5022 break;
5023 }
5024
5025 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe: {
5026 T = S.BuildReadPipeType(T, DeclType.Loc);
5027 processTypeAttrs(state, T, TAL_DeclSpec,
5028 D.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes());
5029 break;
5030 }
5031 }
5032
5033 if (T.isNull()) {
5034 D.setInvalidType(true);
5035 T = Context.IntTy;
5036 }
5037
5038 // See if there are any attributes on this declarator chunk.
5039 processTypeAttrs(state, T, TAL_DeclChunk, DeclType.getAttrs());
5040
5041 if (DeclType.Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Paren) {
5042 if (ExpectNoDerefChunk && !IsNoDerefableChunk(DeclType))
5043 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::warn_noderef_on_non_pointer_or_array);
5044
5045 ExpectNoDerefChunk = state.didParseNoDeref();
5046 }
5047 }
5048
5049 if (ExpectNoDerefChunk)
5050 S.Diag(state.getDeclarator().getBeginLoc(),
5051 diag::warn_noderef_on_non_pointer_or_array);
5052
5053 // GNU warning -Wstrict-prototypes
5054 // Warn if a function declaration is without a prototype.
5055 // This warning is issued for all kinds of unprototyped function
5056 // declarations (i.e. function type typedef, function pointer etc.)
5057 // C99 6.7.5.3p14:
5058 // The empty list in a function declarator that is not part of a definition
5059 // of that function specifies that no information about the number or types
5060 // of the parameters is supplied.
5061 if (!LangOpts.CPlusPlus && D.getFunctionDefinitionKind() == FDK_Declaration) {
5062 bool IsBlock = false;
5063 for (const DeclaratorChunk &DeclType : D.type_objects()) {
5064 switch (DeclType.Kind) {
5065 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
5066 IsBlock = true;
5067 break;
5068 case DeclaratorChunk::Function: {
5069 const DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI = DeclType.Fun;
5070 // We supress the warning when there's no LParen location, as this
5071 // indicates the declaration was an implicit declaration, which gets
5072 // warned about separately via -Wimplicit-function-declaration.
5073 if (FTI.NumParams == 0 && !FTI.isVariadic && FTI.getLParenLoc().isValid())
5074 S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::warn_strict_prototypes)
5075 << IsBlock
5076 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(FTI.getRParenLoc(), "void");
5077 IsBlock = false;
5078 break;
5079 }
5080 default:
5081 break;
5082 }
5083 }
5084 }
5085
5086 assert(!T.isNull() && "T must not be null after this point");
5087
5088 if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && T->isFunctionType()) {
5089 const FunctionProtoType *FnTy = T->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5090 assert(FnTy && "Why oh why is there not a FunctionProtoType here?");
5091
5092 // C++ 8.3.5p4:
5093 // A cv-qualifier-seq shall only be part of the function type
5094 // for a nonstatic member function, the function type to which a pointer
5095 // to member refers, or the top-level function type of a function typedef
5096 // declaration.
5097 //
5098 // Core issue 547 also allows cv-qualifiers on function types that are
5099 // top-level template type arguments.
5100 enum { NonMember, Member, DeductionGuide } Kind = NonMember;
5101 if (D.getName().getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_DeductionGuideName)
5102 Kind = DeductionGuide;
5103 else if (!D.getCXXScopeSpec().isSet()) {
5104 if ((D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext ||
5105 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprContext) &&
5106 !D.getDeclSpec().isFriendSpecified())
5107 Kind = Member;
5108 } else {
5109 DeclContext *DC = S.computeDeclContext(D.getCXXScopeSpec());
5110 if (!DC || DC->isRecord())
5111 Kind = Member;
5112 }
5113
5114 // C++11 [dcl.fct]p6 (w/DR1417):
5115 // An attempt to specify a function type with a cv-qualifier-seq or a
5116 // ref-qualifier (including by typedef-name) is ill-formed unless it is:
5117 // - the function type for a non-static member function,
5118 // - the function type to which a pointer to member refers,
5119 // - the top-level function type of a function typedef declaration or
5120 // alias-declaration,
5121 // - the type-id in the default argument of a type-parameter, or
5122 // - the type-id of a template-argument for a type-parameter
5123 //
5124 // FIXME: Checking this here is insufficient. We accept-invalid on:
5125 //
5126 // template<typename T> struct S { void f(T); };
5127 // S<int() const> s;
5128 //
5129 // ... for instance.
5130 if (IsQualifiedFunction &&
5131 !(Kind == Member &&
5132 D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() != DeclSpec::SCS_static) &&
5133 !IsTypedefName &&
5134 D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::TemplateArgContext &&
5135 D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArgContext) {
5136 SourceLocation Loc = D.getBeginLoc();
5137 SourceRange RemovalRange;
5138 unsigned I;
5139 if (D.isFunctionDeclarator(I)) {
5140 SmallVector<SourceLocation, 4> RemovalLocs;
5141 const DeclaratorChunk &Chunk = D.getTypeObject(I);
5142 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Function);
5143
5144 if (Chunk.Fun.hasRefQualifier())
5145 RemovalLocs.push_back(Chunk.Fun.getRefQualifierLoc());
5146
5147 if (Chunk.Fun.hasMethodTypeQualifiers())
5148 Chunk.Fun.MethodQualifiers->forEachQualifier(
5149 [&](DeclSpec::TQ TypeQual, StringRef QualName,
5150 SourceLocation SL) { RemovalLocs.push_back(SL); });
5151
5152 if (!RemovalLocs.empty()) {
5153 llvm::sort(RemovalLocs,
5154 BeforeThanCompare<SourceLocation>(S.getSourceManager()));
5155 RemovalRange = SourceRange(RemovalLocs.front(), RemovalLocs.back());
5156 Loc = RemovalLocs.front();
5157 }
5158 }
5159
5160 S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_invalid_qualified_function_type)
5161 << Kind << D.isFunctionDeclarator() << T
5162 << getFunctionQualifiersAsString(FnTy)
5163 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(RemovalRange);
5164
5165 // Strip the cv-qualifiers and ref-qualifiers from the type.
5166 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FnTy->getExtProtoInfo();
5167 EPI.TypeQuals.removeCVRQualifiers();
5168 EPI.RefQualifier = RQ_None;
5169
5170 T = Context.getFunctionType(FnTy->getReturnType(), FnTy->getParamTypes(),
5171 EPI);
5172 // Rebuild any parens around the identifier in the function type.
5173 for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
5174 if (D.getTypeObject(i).Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Paren)
5175 break;
5176 T = S.BuildParenType(T);
5177 }
5178 }
5179 }
5180
5181 // Apply any undistributed attributes from the declarator.
5182 processTypeAttrs(state, T, TAL_DeclName, D.getAttributes());
5183
5184 // Diagnose any ignored type attributes.
5185 state.diagnoseIgnoredTypeAttrs(T);
5186
5187 // C++0x [dcl.constexpr]p9:
5188 // A constexpr specifier used in an object declaration declares the object
5189 // as const.
5190 if (D.getDeclSpec().isConstexprSpecified() && T->isObjectType()) {
5191 T.addConst();
5192 }
5193
5194 // If there was an ellipsis in the declarator, the declaration declares a
5195 // parameter pack whose type may be a pack expansion type.
5196 if (D.hasEllipsis()) {
5197 // C++0x [dcl.fct]p13:
5198 // A declarator-id or abstract-declarator containing an ellipsis shall
5199 // only be used in a parameter-declaration. Such a parameter-declaration
5200 // is a parameter pack (14.5.3). [...]
5201 switch (D.getContext()) {
5202 case DeclaratorContext::PrototypeContext:
5203 case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameterContext:
5204 // C++0x [dcl.fct]p13:
5205 // [...] When it is part of a parameter-declaration-clause, the
5206 // parameter pack is a function parameter pack (14.5.3). The type T
5207 // of the declarator-id of the function parameter pack shall contain
5208 // a template parameter pack; each template parameter pack in T is
5209 // expanded by the function parameter pack.
5210 //
5211 // We represent function parameter packs as function parameters whose
5212 // type is a pack expansion.
5213 if (!T->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
5214 S.Diag(D.getEllipsisLoc(),
5215 diag::err_function_parameter_pack_without_parameter_packs)
5216 << T << D.getSourceRange();
5217 D.setEllipsisLoc(SourceLocation());
5218 } else {
5219 T = Context.getPackExpansionType(T, None);
5220 }
5221 break;
5222 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateParamContext:
5223 // C++0x [temp.param]p15:
5224 // If a template-parameter is a [...] is a parameter-declaration that
5225 // declares a parameter pack (8.3.5), then the template-parameter is a
5226 // template parameter pack (14.5.3).
5227 //
5228 // Note: core issue 778 clarifies that, if there are any unexpanded
5229 // parameter packs in the type of the non-type template parameter, then
5230 // it expands those parameter packs.
5231 if (T->containsUnexpandedParameterPack())
5232 T = Context.getPackExpansionType(T, None);
5233 else
5234 S.Diag(D.getEllipsisLoc(),
5235 LangOpts.CPlusPlus11
5236 ? diag::warn_cxx98_compat_variadic_templates
5237 : diag::ext_variadic_templates);
5238 break;
5239
5240 case DeclaratorContext::FileContext:
5241 case DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeListContext:
5242 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameterContext: // FIXME: special diagnostic
5243 // here?
5244 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCResultContext: // FIXME: special diagnostic
5245 // here?
5246 case DeclaratorContext::TypeNameContext:
5247 case DeclaratorContext::FunctionalCastContext:
5248 case DeclaratorContext::CXXNewContext:
5249 case DeclaratorContext::AliasDeclContext:
5250 case DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplateContext:
5251 case DeclaratorContext::MemberContext:
5252 case DeclaratorContext::BlockContext:
5253 case DeclaratorContext::ForContext:
5254 case DeclaratorContext::InitStmtContext:
5255 case DeclaratorContext::ConditionContext:
5256 case DeclaratorContext::CXXCatchContext:
5257 case DeclaratorContext::ObjCCatchContext:
5258 case DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteralContext:
5259 case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprContext:
5260 case DeclaratorContext::ConversionIdContext:
5261 case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnContext:
5262 case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnVarContext:
5263 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateArgContext:
5264 case DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArgContext:
5265 // FIXME: We may want to allow parameter packs in block-literal contexts
5266 // in the future.
5267 S.Diag(D.getEllipsisLoc(),
5268 diag::err_ellipsis_in_declarator_not_parameter);
5269 D.setEllipsisLoc(SourceLocation());
5270 break;
5271 }
5272 }
5273
5274 assert(!T.isNull() && "T must not be null at the end of this function");
5275 if (D.isInvalidType() || IsIntegerPointerInPureCapABI)
5276 return Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T);
5277
5278 return GetTypeSourceInfoForDeclarator(state, T, TInfo);
5279}
5280
5281/// GetTypeForDeclarator - Convert the type for the specified
5282/// declarator to Type instances.
5283///
5284/// The result of this call will never be null, but the associated
5285/// type may be a null type if there's an unrecoverable error.
5286TypeSourceInfo *Sema::GetTypeForDeclarator(Declarator &D, Scope *S) {
5287 // Determine the type of the declarator. Not all forms of declarator
5288 // have a type.
5289
5290 TypeProcessingState state(*this, D);
5291
5292 TypeSourceInfo *ReturnTypeInfo = nullptr;
5293 QualType T = GetDeclSpecTypeForDeclarator(state, ReturnTypeInfo);
5294 if (D.isPrototypeContext() && getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
5295 inferARCWriteback(state, T);
5296
5297 return GetFullTypeForDeclarator(state, T, ReturnTypeInfo);
5298}
5299
5300static void transferARCOwnershipToDeclSpec(Sema &S,
5301 QualType &declSpecTy,
5302 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership) {
5303 if (declSpecTy->isObjCRetainableType() &&
5304 declSpecTy.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_None) {
5305 Qualifiers qs;
5306 qs.addObjCLifetime(ownership);
5307 declSpecTy = S.Context.getQualifiedType(declSpecTy, qs);
5308 }
5309}
5310
5311static void transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(TypeProcessingState &state,
5312 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership,
5313 unsigned chunkIndex) {
5314 Sema &S = state.getSema();
5315 Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
5316
5317 // Look for an explicit lifetime attribute.
5318 DeclaratorChunk &chunk = D.getTypeObject(chunkIndex);
5319 if (chunk.getAttrs().hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership))
5320 return;
5321
5322 const char *attrStr = nullptr;
5323 switch (ownership) {
5324 case Qualifiers::OCL_None: llvm_unreachable("no ownership!");
5325 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone: attrStr = "none"; break;
5326 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong: attrStr = "strong"; break;
5327 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak: attrStr = "weak"; break;
5328 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing: attrStr = "autoreleasing"; break;
5329 }
5330
5331 IdentifierLoc *Arg = new (S.Context) IdentifierLoc;
5332 Arg->Ident = &S.Context.Idents.get(attrStr);
5333 Arg->Loc = SourceLocation();
5334
5335 ArgsUnion Args(Arg);
5336
5337 // If there wasn't one, add one (with an invalid source location
5338 // so that we don't make an AttributedType for it).
5339 ParsedAttr *attr = D.getAttributePool().create(
5340 &S.Context.Idents.get("objc_ownership"), SourceLocation(),
5341 /*scope*/ nullptr, SourceLocation(),
5342 /*args*/ &Args, 1, ParsedAttr::AS_GNU);
5343 chunk.getAttrs().addAtEnd(attr);
5344 // TODO: mark whether we did this inference?
5345}
5346
5347/// Used for transferring ownership in casts resulting in l-values.
5348static void transferARCOwnership(TypeProcessingState &state,
5349 QualType &declSpecTy,
5350 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership) {
5351 Sema &S = state.getSema();
5352 Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
5353
5354 int inner = -1;
5355 bool hasIndirection = false;
5356 for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
5357 DeclaratorChunk &chunk = D.getTypeObject(i);
5358 switch (chunk.Kind) {
5359 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
5360 // Ignore parens.
5361 break;
5362
5363 case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
5364 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
5365 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
5366 if (inner != -1)
5367 hasIndirection = true;
5368 inner = i;
5369 break;
5370
5371 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
5372 if (inner != -1)
5373 transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(state, ownership, i);
5374 return;
5375
5376 case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
5377 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
5378 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
5379 return;
5380 }
5381 }
5382
5383 if (inner == -1)
5384 return;
5385
5386 DeclaratorChunk &chunk = D.getTypeObject(inner);
5387 if (chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pointer) {
5388 if (declSpecTy->isObjCRetainableType())
5389 return transferARCOwnershipToDeclSpec(S, declSpecTy, ownership);
5390 if (declSpecTy->isObjCObjectType() && hasIndirection)
5391 return transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(state, ownership, inner);
5392 } else {
5393 assert(chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Array ||
5394 chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Reference);
5395 return transferARCOwnershipToDeclSpec(S, declSpecTy, ownership);
5396 }
5397}
5398
5399TypeSourceInfo *Sema::GetTypeForDeclaratorCast(Declarator &D, QualType FromTy) {
5400 TypeProcessingState state(*this, D);
5401
5402 TypeSourceInfo *ReturnTypeInfo = nullptr;
5403 QualType declSpecTy = GetDeclSpecTypeForDeclarator(state, ReturnTypeInfo);
5404
5405 if (getLangOpts().ObjC) {
5406 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership = Context.getInnerObjCOwnership(FromTy);
5407 if (ownership != Qualifiers::OCL_None)
5408 transferARCOwnership(state, declSpecTy, ownership);
5409 }
5410
5411 return GetFullTypeForDeclarator(state, declSpecTy, ReturnTypeInfo);
5412}
5413
5414static void fillAttributedTypeLoc(AttributedTypeLoc TL,
5415 TypeProcessingState &State) {
5416 TL.setAttr(State.takeAttrForAttributedType(TL.getTypePtr()));
5417}
5418
5419namespace {
5420 class TypeSpecLocFiller : public TypeLocVisitor<TypeSpecLocFiller> {
5421 ASTContext &Context;
5422 TypeProcessingState &State;
5423 const DeclSpec &DS;
5424
5425 public:
5426 TypeSpecLocFiller(ASTContext &Context, TypeProcessingState &State,
5427 const DeclSpec &DS)
5428 : Context(Context), State(State), DS(DS) {}
5429
5430 void VisitAttributedTypeLoc(AttributedTypeLoc TL) {
5431 Visit(TL.getModifiedLoc());
5432 fillAttributedTypeLoc(TL, State);
5433 }
5434 void VisitMacroQualifiedTypeLoc(MacroQualifiedTypeLoc TL) {
5435 Visit(TL.getInnerLoc());
5436 TL.setExpansionLoc(
5437 State.getExpansionLocForMacroQualifiedType(TL.getTypePtr()));
5438 }
5439 void VisitQualifiedTypeLoc(QualifiedTypeLoc TL) {
5440 Visit(TL.getUnqualifiedLoc());
5441 }
5442 void VisitTypedefTypeLoc(TypedefTypeLoc TL) {
5443 TL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5444 }
5445 void VisitObjCInterfaceTypeLoc(ObjCInterfaceTypeLoc TL) {
5446 TL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5447 // FIXME. We should have DS.getTypeSpecTypeEndLoc(). But, it requires
5448 // addition field. What we have is good enough for dispay of location
5449 // of 'fixit' on interface name.
5450 TL.setNameEndLoc(DS.getEndLoc());
5451 }
5452 void VisitObjCObjectTypeLoc(ObjCObjectTypeLoc TL) {
5453 TypeSourceInfo *RepTInfo = nullptr;
5454 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &RepTInfo);
5455 TL.copy(RepTInfo->getTypeLoc());
5456 }
5457 void VisitObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc(ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc TL) {
5458 TypeSourceInfo *RepTInfo = nullptr;
5459 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &RepTInfo);
5460 TL.copy(RepTInfo->getTypeLoc());
5461 }
5462 void VisitTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc(TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL) {
5463 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
5464 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
5465
5466 // If we got no declarator info from previous Sema routines,
5467 // just fill with the typespec loc.
5468 if (!TInfo) {
5469 TL.initialize(Context, DS.getTypeSpecTypeNameLoc());
5470 return;
5471 }
5472
5473 TypeLoc OldTL = TInfo->getTypeLoc();
5474 if (TInfo->getType()->getAs<ElaboratedType>()) {
5475 ElaboratedTypeLoc ElabTL = OldTL.castAs<ElaboratedTypeLoc>();
5476 TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc NamedTL = ElabTL.getNamedTypeLoc()
5477 .castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>();
5478 TL.copy(NamedTL);
5479 } else {
5480 TL.copy(OldTL.castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>());
5481 assert(TL.getRAngleLoc() == OldTL.castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>().getRAngleLoc());
5482 }
5483
5484 }
5485 void VisitTypeOfExprTypeLoc(TypeOfExprTypeLoc TL) {
5486 assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_typeofExpr);
5487 TL.setTypeofLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5488 TL.setParensRange(DS.getTypeofParensRange());
5489 }
5490 void VisitTypeOfTypeLoc(TypeOfTypeLoc TL) {
5491 assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_typeofType);
5492 TL.setTypeofLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5493 TL.setParensRange(DS.getTypeofParensRange());
5494 assert(DS.getRepAsType());
5495 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
5496 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
5497 TL.setUnderlyingTInfo(TInfo);
5498 }
5499 void VisitUnaryTransformTypeLoc(UnaryTransformTypeLoc TL) {
5500 // FIXME: This holds only because we only have one unary transform.
5501 assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_underlyingType);
5502 TL.setKWLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5503 TL.setParensRange(DS.getTypeofParensRange());
5504 assert(DS.getRepAsType());
5505 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
5506 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
5507 TL.setUnderlyingTInfo(TInfo);
5508 }
5509 void VisitBuiltinTypeLoc(BuiltinTypeLoc TL) {
5510 // By default, use the source location of the type specifier.
5511 TL.setBuiltinLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5512 if (TL.needsExtraLocalData()) {
5513 // Set info for the written builtin specifiers.
5514 TL.getWrittenBuiltinSpecs() = DS.getWrittenBuiltinSpecs();
5515 // Try to have a meaningful source location.
5516 if (TL.getWrittenSignSpec() != TSS_unspecified)
5517 TL.expandBuiltinRange(DS.getTypeSpecSignLoc());
5518 if (TL.getWrittenWidthSpec() != TSW_unspecified)
5519 TL.expandBuiltinRange(DS.getTypeSpecWidthRange());
5520 }
5521 }
5522 void VisitElaboratedTypeLoc(ElaboratedTypeLoc TL) {
5523 ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword
5524 = TypeWithKeyword::getKeywordForTypeSpec(DS.getTypeSpecType());
5525 if (DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_typename) {
5526 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
5527 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
5528 if (TInfo) {
5529 TL.copy(TInfo->getTypeLoc().castAs<ElaboratedTypeLoc>());
5530 return;
5531 }
5532 }
5533 TL.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(Keyword != ETK_None
5534 ? DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc()
5535 : SourceLocation());
5536 const CXXScopeSpec& SS = DS.getTypeSpecScope();
5537 TL.setQualifierLoc(SS.getWithLocInContext(Context));
5538 Visit(TL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc());
5539 }
5540 void VisitDependentNameTypeLoc(DependentNameTypeLoc TL) {
5541 assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_typename);
5542 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
5543 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
5544 assert(TInfo);
5545 TL.copy(TInfo->getTypeLoc().castAs<DependentNameTypeLoc>());
5546 }
5547 void VisitDependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc(
5548 DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL) {
5549 assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_typename);
5550 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
5551 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
5552 assert(TInfo);
5553 TL.copy(
5554 TInfo->getTypeLoc().castAs<DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>());
5555 }
5556 void VisitTagTypeLoc(TagTypeLoc TL) {
5557 TL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeNameLoc());
5558 }
5559 void VisitAtomicTypeLoc(AtomicTypeLoc TL) {
5560 // An AtomicTypeLoc can come from either an _Atomic(...) type specifier
5561 // or an _Atomic qualifier.
5562 if (DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_atomic) {
5563 TL.setKWLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5564 TL.setParensRange(DS.getTypeofParensRange());
5565
5566 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
5567 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
5568 assert(TInfo);
5569 TL.getValueLoc().initializeFullCopy(TInfo->getTypeLoc());
5570 } else {
5571 TL.setKWLoc(DS.getAtomicSpecLoc());
5572 // No parens, to indicate this was spelled as an _Atomic qualifier.
5573 TL.setParensRange(SourceRange());
5574 Visit(TL.getValueLoc());
5575 }
5576 }
5577
5578 void VisitPipeTypeLoc(PipeTypeLoc TL) {
5579 TL.setKWLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5580
5581 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
5582 Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
5583 TL.getValueLoc().initializeFullCopy(TInfo->getTypeLoc());
5584 }
5585
5586 void VisitTypeLoc(TypeLoc TL) {
5587 // FIXME: add other typespec types and change this to an assert.
5588 TL.initialize(Context, DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5589 }
5590 };
5591
5592 class DeclaratorLocFiller : public TypeLocVisitor<DeclaratorLocFiller> {
5593 ASTContext &Context;
5594 TypeProcessingState &State;
5595 const DeclaratorChunk &Chunk;
5596
5597 public:
5598 DeclaratorLocFiller(ASTContext &Context, TypeProcessingState &State,
5599 const DeclaratorChunk &Chunk)
5600 : Context(Context), State(State), Chunk(Chunk) {}
5601
5602 void VisitQualifiedTypeLoc(QualifiedTypeLoc TL) {
5603 llvm_unreachable("qualified type locs not expected here!");
5604 }
5605 void VisitDecayedTypeLoc(DecayedTypeLoc TL) {
5606 llvm_unreachable("decayed type locs not expected here!");
5607 }
5608
5609 void VisitAttributedTypeLoc(AttributedTypeLoc TL) {
5610 fillAttributedTypeLoc(TL, State);
5611 }
5612 void VisitAdjustedTypeLoc(AdjustedTypeLoc TL) {
5613 // nothing
5614 }
5615 void VisitBlockPointerTypeLoc(BlockPointerTypeLoc TL) {
5616 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer);
5617 TL.setCaretLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5618 }
5619 void VisitPointerTypeLoc(PointerTypeLoc TL) {
5620 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pointer);
5621 TL.setStarLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5622 }
5623 void VisitObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc(ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc TL) {
5624 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pointer);
5625 TL.setStarLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5626 }
5627 void VisitMemberPointerTypeLoc(MemberPointerTypeLoc TL) {
5628 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer);
5629 const CXXScopeSpec& SS = Chunk.Mem.Scope();
5630 NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNSLoc = SS.getWithLocInContext(Context);
5631
5632 const Type* ClsTy = TL.getClass();
5633 QualType ClsQT = QualType(ClsTy, 0);
5634 TypeSourceInfo *ClsTInfo = Context.CreateTypeSourceInfo(ClsQT, 0);
5635 // Now copy source location info into the type loc component.
5636 TypeLoc ClsTL = ClsTInfo->getTypeLoc();
5637 switch (NNSLoc.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getKind()) {
5638 case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
5639 assert(isa<DependentNameType>(ClsTy) && "Unexpected TypeLoc");
5640 {
5641 DependentNameTypeLoc DNTLoc = ClsTL.castAs<DependentNameTypeLoc>();
5642 DNTLoc.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(SourceLocation());
5643 DNTLoc.setQualifierLoc(NNSLoc.getPrefix());
5644 DNTLoc.setNameLoc(NNSLoc.getLocalBeginLoc());
5645 }
5646 break;
5647
5648 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
5649 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
5650 if (isa<ElaboratedType>(ClsTy)) {
5651 ElaboratedTypeLoc ETLoc = ClsTL.castAs<ElaboratedTypeLoc>();
5652 ETLoc.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(SourceLocation());
5653 ETLoc.setQualifierLoc(NNSLoc.getPrefix());
5654 TypeLoc NamedTL = ETLoc.getNamedTypeLoc();
5655 NamedTL.initializeFullCopy(NNSLoc.getTypeLoc());
5656 } else {
5657 ClsTL.initializeFullCopy(NNSLoc.getTypeLoc());
5658 }
5659 break;
5660
5661 case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
5662 case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
5663 case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
5664 case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
5665 llvm_unreachable("Nested-name-specifier must name a type");
5666 }
5667
5668 // Finally fill in MemberPointerLocInfo fields.
5669 TL.setStarLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5670 TL.setClassTInfo(ClsTInfo);
5671 }
5672 void VisitLValueReferenceTypeLoc(LValueReferenceTypeLoc TL) {
5673 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Reference);
5674 // 'Amp' is misleading: this might have been originally
5675 /// spelled with AmpAmp.
5676 TL.setAmpLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5677 }
5678 void VisitRValueReferenceTypeLoc(RValueReferenceTypeLoc TL) {
5679 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Reference);
5680 assert(!Chunk.Ref.LValueRef);
5681 TL.setAmpAmpLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5682 }
5683 void VisitArrayTypeLoc(ArrayTypeLoc TL) {
5684 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Array);
5685 TL.setLBracketLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5686 TL.setRBracketLoc(Chunk.EndLoc);
5687 TL.setSizeExpr(static_cast<Expr*>(Chunk.Arr.NumElts));
5688 }
5689 void VisitFunctionTypeLoc(FunctionTypeLoc TL) {
5690 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Function);
5691 TL.setLocalRangeBegin(Chunk.Loc);
5692 TL.setLocalRangeEnd(Chunk.EndLoc);
5693
5694 const DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI = Chunk.Fun;
5695 TL.setLParenLoc(FTI.getLParenLoc());
5696 TL.setRParenLoc(FTI.getRParenLoc());
5697 for (unsigned i = 0, e = TL.getNumParams(), tpi = 0; i != e; ++i) {
5698 ParmVarDecl *Param = cast<ParmVarDecl>(FTI.Params[i].Param);
5699 TL.setParam(tpi++, Param);
5700 }
5701 TL.setExceptionSpecRange(FTI.getExceptionSpecRange());
5702 }
5703 void VisitParenTypeLoc(ParenTypeLoc TL) {
5704 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Paren);
5705 TL.setLParenLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5706 TL.setRParenLoc(Chunk.EndLoc);
5707 }
5708 void VisitPipeTypeLoc(PipeTypeLoc TL) {
5709 assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pipe);
5710 TL.setKWLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5711 }
5712 void VisitMacroQualifiedTypeLoc(MacroQualifiedTypeLoc TL) {
5713 TL.setExpansionLoc(Chunk.Loc);
5714 }
5715
5716 void VisitTypeLoc(TypeLoc TL) {
5717 llvm_unreachable("unsupported TypeLoc kind in declarator!");
5718 }
5719 };
5720} // end anonymous namespace
5721
5722static void fillAtomicQualLoc(AtomicTypeLoc ATL, const DeclaratorChunk &Chunk) {
5723 SourceLocation Loc;
5724 switch (Chunk.Kind) {
5725 case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
5726 case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
5727 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
5728 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
5729 llvm_unreachable("cannot be _Atomic qualified");
5730
5731 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
5732 Loc = SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(Chunk.Ptr.AtomicQualLoc);
5733 break;
5734
5735 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
5736 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
5737 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
5738 // FIXME: Provide a source location for the _Atomic keyword.
5739 break;
5740 }
5741
5742 ATL.setKWLoc(Loc);
5743 ATL.setParensRange(SourceRange());
5744}
5745
5746static void
5747fillDependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc(DependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc DASTL,
5748 const ParsedAttributesView &Attrs) {
5749 for (const ParsedAttr &AL : Attrs) {
5750 if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_AddressSpace) {
5751 DASTL.setAttrNameLoc(AL.getLoc());
5752 DASTL.setAttrExprOperand(AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
5753 DASTL.setAttrOperandParensRange(SourceRange());
5754 return;
5755 }
5756 }
5757
5758 llvm_unreachable(
5759 "no address_space attribute found at the expected location!");
5760}
5761
5762/// Create and instantiate a TypeSourceInfo with type source information.
5763///
5764/// \param T QualType referring to the type as written in source code.
5765///
5766/// \param ReturnTypeInfo For declarators whose return type does not show
5767/// up in the normal place in the declaration specifiers (such as a C++
5768/// conversion function), this pointer will refer to a type source information
5769/// for that return type.
5770static TypeSourceInfo *
5771GetTypeSourceInfoForDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &State,
5772 QualType T, TypeSourceInfo *ReturnTypeInfo) {
5773 Sema &S = State.getSema();
5774 Declarator &D = State.getDeclarator();
5775
5776 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = S.Context.CreateTypeSourceInfo(T);
5777 UnqualTypeLoc CurrTL = TInfo->getTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
5778
5779 // Handle parameter packs whose type is a pack expansion.
5780 if (isa<PackExpansionType>(T)) {
5781 CurrTL.castAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>().setEllipsisLoc(D.getEllipsisLoc());
5782 CurrTL = CurrTL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
5783 }
5784
5785 for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
5786 // An AtomicTypeLoc might be produced by an atomic qualifier in this
5787 // declarator chunk.
5788 if (AtomicTypeLoc ATL = CurrTL.getAs<AtomicTypeLoc>()) {
5789 fillAtomicQualLoc(ATL, D.getTypeObject(i));
5790 CurrTL = ATL.getValueLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
5791 }
5792
5793 while (MacroQualifiedTypeLoc TL = CurrTL.getAs<MacroQualifiedTypeLoc>()) {
5794 TL.setExpansionLoc(
5795 State.getExpansionLocForMacroQualifiedType(TL.getTypePtr()));
5796 CurrTL = TL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
5797 }
5798
5799 while (AttributedTypeLoc TL = CurrTL.getAs<AttributedTypeLoc>()) {
5800 fillAttributedTypeLoc(TL, State);
5801 CurrTL = TL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
5802 }
5803
5804 while (DependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc TL =
5805 CurrTL.getAs<DependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc>()) {
5806 fillDependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc(TL, D.getTypeObject(i).getAttrs());
5807 CurrTL = TL.getPointeeTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
5808 }
5809
5810 // FIXME: Ordering here?
5811 while (AdjustedTypeLoc TL = CurrTL.getAs<AdjustedTypeLoc>())
5812 CurrTL = TL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
5813
5814 DeclaratorLocFiller(S.Context, State, D.getTypeObject(i)).Visit(CurrTL);
5815 CurrTL = CurrTL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
5816 }
5817
5818 // If we have different source information for the return type, use
5819 // that. This really only applies to C++ conversion functions.
5820 if (ReturnTypeInfo) {
5821 TypeLoc TL = ReturnTypeInfo->getTypeLoc();
5822 assert(TL.getFullDataSize() == CurrTL.getFullDataSize());
5823 memcpy(CurrTL.getOpaqueData(), TL.getOpaqueData(), TL.getFullDataSize());
5824 } else {
5825 TypeSpecLocFiller(S.Context, State, D.getDeclSpec()).Visit(CurrTL);
5826 }
5827
5828 return TInfo;
5829}
5830
5831/// Create a LocInfoType to hold the given QualType and TypeSourceInfo.
5832ParsedType Sema::CreateParsedType(QualType T, TypeSourceInfo *TInfo) {
5833 // FIXME: LocInfoTypes are "transient", only needed for passing to/from Parser
5834 // and Sema during declaration parsing. Try deallocating/caching them when
5835 // it's appropriate, instead of allocating them and keeping them around.
5836 LocInfoType *LocT = (LocInfoType*)BumpAlloc.Allocate(sizeof(LocInfoType),
5837 TypeAlignment);
5838 new (LocT) LocInfoType(T, TInfo);
5839 assert(LocT->getTypeClass() != T->getTypeClass() &&
5840 "LocInfoType's TypeClass conflicts with an existing Type class");
5841 return ParsedType::make(QualType(LocT, 0));
5842}
5843
5844void LocInfoType::getAsStringInternal(std::string &Str,
5845 const PrintingPolicy &Policy) const {
5846 llvm_unreachable("LocInfoType leaked into the type system; an opaque TypeTy*"
5847 " was used directly instead of getting the QualType through"
5848 " GetTypeFromParser");
5849}
5850
5851TypeResult Sema::ActOnTypeName(Scope *S, Declarator &D) {
5852 // C99 6.7.6: Type names have no identifier. This is already validated by
5853 // the parser.
5854 assert(D.getIdentifier() == nullptr &&
5855 "Type name should have no identifier!");
5856
5857 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = GetTypeForDeclarator(D, S);
5858 QualType T = TInfo->getType();
5859 if (D.isInvalidType())
5860 return true;
5861
5862 // Make sure there are no unused decl attributes on the declarator.
5863 // We don't want to do this for ObjC parameters because we're going
5864 // to apply them to the actual parameter declaration.
5865 // Likewise, we don't want to do this for alias declarations, because
5866 // we are actually going to build a declaration from this eventually.
5867 if (D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameterContext &&
5868 D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::AliasDeclContext &&
5869 D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplateContext)
5870 checkUnusedDeclAttributes(D);
5871
5872 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5873 // Check that there are no default arguments (C++ only).
5874 CheckExtraCXXDefaultArguments(D);
5875 }
5876
5877 return CreateParsedType(T, TInfo);
5878}
5879
5880ParsedType Sema::ActOnObjCInstanceType(SourceLocation Loc) {
5881 QualType T = Context.getObjCInstanceType();
5882 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, Loc);
5883 return CreateParsedType(T, TInfo);
5884}
5885
5886//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5887// Type Attribute Processing
5888//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5889
5890/// Build an AddressSpace index from a constant expression and diagnose any
5891/// errors related to invalid address_spaces. Returns true on successfully
5892/// building an AddressSpace index.
5893static bool BuildAddressSpaceIndex(Sema &S, LangAS &ASIdx,
5894 const Expr *AddrSpace,
5895 SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
5896 if (!AddrSpace->isValueDependent()) {
5897 llvm::APSInt addrSpace(32);
5898 if (!AddrSpace->isIntegerConstantExpr(addrSpace, S.Context)) {
5899 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
5900 << "'address_space'" << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
5901 << AddrSpace->getSourceRange();
5902 return false;
5903 }
5904
5905 // Bounds checking.
5906 if (addrSpace.isSigned()) {
5907 if (addrSpace.isNegative()) {
5908 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_address_space_negative)
5909 << AddrSpace->getSourceRange();
5910 return false;
5911 }
5912 addrSpace.setIsSigned(false);
5913 }
5914
5915 llvm::APSInt max(addrSpace.getBitWidth());
5916 max =
5917 Qualifiers::MaxAddressSpace - (unsigned)LangAS::FirstTargetAddressSpace;
5918 if (addrSpace > max) {
5919 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_address_space_too_high)
5920 << (unsigned)max.getZExtValue() << AddrSpace->getSourceRange();
5921 return false;
5922 }
5923
5924 ASIdx =
5925 getLangASFromTargetAS(static_cast<unsigned>(addrSpace.getZExtValue()));
5926 return true;
5927 }
5928
5929 // Default value for DependentAddressSpaceTypes
5930 ASIdx = LangAS::Default;
5931 return true;
5932}
5933
5934/// BuildAddressSpaceAttr - Builds a DependentAddressSpaceType if an expression
5935/// is uninstantiated. If instantiated it will apply the appropriate address
5936/// space to the type. This function allows dependent template variables to be
5937/// used in conjunction with the address_space attribute
5938QualType Sema::BuildAddressSpaceAttr(QualType &T, LangAS ASIdx, Expr *AddrSpace,
5939 SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
5940 if (!AddrSpace->isValueDependent()) {
5941 if (DiagnoseMultipleAddrSpaceAttributes(*this, T.getAddressSpace(), ASIdx,
5942 AttrLoc))
5943 return QualType();
5944
5945 return Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(T, ASIdx);
5946 }
5947
5948 // A check with similar intentions as checking if a type already has an
5949 // address space except for on a dependent types, basically if the
5950 // current type is already a DependentAddressSpaceType then its already
5951 // lined up to have another address space on it and we can't have
5952 // multiple address spaces on the one pointer indirection
5953 if (T->getAs<DependentAddressSpaceType>()) {
5954 Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_address_multiple_qualifiers);
5955 return QualType();
5956 }
5957
5958 return Context.getDependentAddressSpaceType(T, AddrSpace, AttrLoc);
5959}
5960
5961QualType Sema::BuildAddressSpaceAttr(QualType &T, Expr *AddrSpace,
5962 SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
5963 LangAS ASIdx;
5964 if (!BuildAddressSpaceIndex(*this, ASIdx, AddrSpace, AttrLoc))
5965 return QualType();
5966 return BuildAddressSpaceAttr(T, ASIdx, AddrSpace, AttrLoc);
5967}
5968
5969/// HandleAddressSpaceTypeAttribute - Process an address_space attribute on the
5970/// specified type. The attribute contains 1 argument, the id of the address
5971/// space for the type.
5972static void HandleAddressSpaceTypeAttribute(QualType &Type,
5973 const ParsedAttr &Attr,
5974 TypeProcessingState &State) {
5975 Sema &S = State.getSema();
5976
5977 // ISO/IEC TR 18037 S5.3 (amending C99 6.7.3): "A function type shall not be
5978 // qualified by an address-space qualifier."
5979 if (Type->isFunctionType() && !S.Context.getTargetInfo().SupportsCapabilities()) {
5980 // FIXME: We should only allow function pointers to be qualified with an AS
5981 // if it's the capability AS, but for now allow them to be any AS when the
5982 // target supports capabilities.
5983 S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_address_function_type);
5984 Attr.setInvalid();
5985 return;
5986 }
5987
5988 LangAS ASIdx;
5989 if (Attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_AddressSpace) {
5990
5991 // Check the attribute arguments.
5992 if (Attr.getNumArgs() != 1) {
5993 S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << Attr
5994 << 1;
5995 Attr.setInvalid();
5996 return;
5997 }
5998
5999 Expr *ASArgExpr;
6000 if (Attr.isArgIdent(0)) {
6001 // Special case where the argument is a template id.
6002 CXXScopeSpec SS;
6003 SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc;
6004 UnqualifiedId id;
6005 id.setIdentifier(Attr.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident, Attr.getLoc());
6006
6007 ExprResult AddrSpace = S.ActOnIdExpression(
6008 S.getCurScope(), SS, TemplateKWLoc, id, /*HasTrailingLParen=*/false,
6009 /*IsAddressOfOperand=*/false);
6010 if (AddrSpace.isInvalid())
6011 return;
6012
6013 ASArgExpr = static_cast<Expr *>(AddrSpace.get());
6014 } else {
6015 ASArgExpr = static_cast<Expr *>(Attr.getArgAsExpr(0));
6016 }
6017
6018 LangAS ASIdx;
6019 if (!BuildAddressSpaceIndex(S, ASIdx, ASArgExpr, Attr.getLoc())) {
6020 Attr.setInvalid();
6021 return;
6022 }
6023
6024 ASTContext &Ctx = S.Context;
6025 auto *ASAttr = ::new (Ctx) AddressSpaceAttr(
6026 Attr.getRange(), Ctx, Attr.getAttributeSpellingListIndex(),
6027 static_cast<unsigned>(ASIdx));
6028
6029 // If the expression is not value dependent (not templated), then we can
6030 // apply the address space qualifiers just to the equivalent type.
6031 // Otherwise, we make an AttributedType with the modified and equivalent
6032 // type the same, and wrap it in a DependentAddressSpaceType. When this
6033 // dependent type is resolved, the qualifier is added to the equivalent type
6034 // later.
6035 QualType T;
6036 if (!ASArgExpr->isValueDependent()) {
6037 QualType EquivType =
6038 S.BuildAddressSpaceAttr(Type, ASIdx, ASArgExpr, Attr.getLoc());
6039 if (EquivType.isNull()) {
6040 Attr.setInvalid();
6041 return;
6042 }
6043 T = State.getAttributedType(ASAttr, Type, EquivType);
6044 } else {
6045 T = State.getAttributedType(ASAttr, Type, Type);
6046 T = S.BuildAddressSpaceAttr(T, ASIdx, ASArgExpr, Attr.getLoc());
6047 }
6048
6049 if (!T.isNull())
6050 Type = T;
6051 else
6052 Attr.setInvalid();
6053 } else {
6054 // The keyword-based type attributes imply which address space to use.
6055 ASIdx = Attr.asOpenCLLangAS();
6056 if (ASIdx == LangAS::Default)
6057 llvm_unreachable("Invalid address space");
6058
6059 if (DiagnoseMultipleAddrSpaceAttributes(S, Type.getAddressSpace(), ASIdx,
6060 Attr.getLoc())) {
6061 Attr.setInvalid();
6062 return;
6063 }
6064
6065 Type = S.Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(Type, ASIdx);
6066 }
6067}
6068
6069/// Does this type have a "direct" ownership qualifier? That is,
6070/// is it written like "__strong id", as opposed to something like
6071/// "typeof(foo)", where that happens to be strong?
6072static bool hasDirectOwnershipQualifier(QualType type) {
6073 // Fast path: no qualifier at all.
6074 assert(type.getQualifiers().hasObjCLifetime());
6075
6076 while (true) {
6077 // __strong id
6078 if (const AttributedType *attr = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(type)) {
6079 if (attr->getAttrKind() == attr::ObjCOwnership)
6080 return true;
6081
6082 type = attr->getModifiedType();
6083
6084 // X *__strong (...)
6085 } else if (const ParenType *paren = dyn_cast<ParenType>(type)) {
6086 type = paren->getInnerType();
6087
6088 // That's it for things we want to complain about. In particular,
6089 // we do not want to look through typedefs, typeof(expr),
6090 // typeof(type), or any other way that the type is somehow
6091 // abstracted.
6092 } else {
6093
6094 return false;
6095 }
6096 }
6097}
6098
6099/// handleObjCOwnershipTypeAttr - Process an objc_ownership
6100/// attribute on the specified type.
6101///
6102/// Returns 'true' if the attribute was handled.
6103static bool handleObjCOwnershipTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state,
6104 ParsedAttr &attr, QualType &type) {
6105 bool NonObjCPointer = false;
6106
6107 if (!type->isDependentType() && !type->isUndeducedType()) {
6108 if (const PointerType *ptr = type->getAs<PointerType>()) {
6109 QualType pointee = ptr->getPointeeType();
6110 if (pointee->isObjCRetainableType() || pointee->isPointerType())
6111 return false;
6112 // It is important not to lose the source info that there was an attribute
6113 // applied to non-objc pointer. We will create an attributed type but
6114 // its type will be the same as the original type.
6115 NonObjCPointer = true;
6116 } else if (!type->isObjCRetainableType()) {
6117 return false;
6118 }
6119
6120 // Don't accept an ownership attribute in the declspec if it would
6121 // just be the return type of a block pointer.
6122 if (state.isProcessingDeclSpec()) {
6123 Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
6124 if (maybeMovePastReturnType(D, D.getNumTypeObjects(),
6125 /*onlyBlockPointers=*/true))
6126 return false;
6127 }
6128 }
6129
6130 Sema &S = state.getSema();
6131 SourceLocation AttrLoc = attr.getLoc();
6132 if (AttrLoc.isMacroID())
6133 AttrLoc =
6134 S.getSourceManager().getImmediateExpansionRange(AttrLoc).getBegin();
6135
6136 if (!attr.isArgIdent(0)) {
6137 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type) << attr
6138 << AANT_ArgumentString;
6139 attr.setInvalid();
6140 return true;
6141 }
6142
6143 IdentifierInfo *II = attr.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
6144 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime lifetime;
6145 if (II->isStr("none"))
6146 lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone;
6147 else if (II->isStr("strong"))
6148 lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_Strong;
6149 else if (II->isStr("weak"))
6150 lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_Weak;
6151 else if (II->isStr("autoreleasing"))
6152 lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing;
6153 else {
6154 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)
6155 << attr.getName() << II;
6156 attr.setInvalid();
6157 return true;
6158 }
6159
6160 // Just ignore lifetime attributes other than __weak and __unsafe_unretained
6161 // outside of ARC mode.
6162 if (!S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
6163 lifetime != Qualifiers::OCL_Weak &&
6164 lifetime != Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone) {
6165 return true;
6166 }
6167
6168 SplitQualType underlyingType = type.split();
6169
6170 // Check for redundant/conflicting ownership qualifiers.
6171 if (Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime previousLifetime
6172 = type.getQualifiers().getObjCLifetime()) {
6173 // If it's written directly, that's an error.
6174 if (hasDirectOwnershipQualifier(type)) {
6175 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attr_objc_ownership_redundant)
6176 << type;
6177 return true;
6178 }
6179
6180 // Otherwise, if the qualifiers actually conflict, pull sugar off
6181 // and remove the ObjCLifetime qualifiers.
6182 if (previousLifetime != lifetime) {
6183 // It's possible to have multiple local ObjCLifetime qualifiers. We
6184 // can't stop after we reach a type that is directly qualified.
6185 const Type *prevTy = nullptr;
6186 while (!prevTy || prevTy != underlyingType.Ty) {
6187 prevTy = underlyingType.Ty;
6188 underlyingType = underlyingType.getSingleStepDesugaredType();
6189 }
6190 underlyingType.Quals.removeObjCLifetime();
6191 }
6192 }
6193
6194 underlyingType.Quals.addObjCLifetime(lifetime);
6195
6196 if (NonObjCPointer) {
6197 StringRef name = attr.getName()->getName();
6198 switch (lifetime) {
6199 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
6200 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
6201 break;
6202 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong: name = "__strong"; break;
6203 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak: name = "__weak"; break;
6204 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing: name = "__autoreleasing"; break;
6205 }
6206 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_type_attribute_wrong_type) << name
6207 << TDS_ObjCObjOrBlock << type;
6208 }
6209
6210 // Don't actually add the __unsafe_unretained qualifier in non-ARC files,
6211 // because having both 'T' and '__unsafe_unretained T' exist in the type
6212 // system causes unfortunate widespread consistency problems. (For example,
6213 // they're not considered compatible types, and we mangle them identicially
6214 // as template arguments.) These problems are all individually fixable,
6215 // but it's easier to just not add the qualifier and instead sniff it out
6216 // in specific places using isObjCInertUnsafeUnretainedType().
6217 //
6218 // Doing this does means we miss some trivial consistency checks that
6219 // would've triggered in ARC, but that's better than trying to solve all
6220 // the coexistence problems with __unsafe_unretained.
6221 if (!S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
6222 lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone) {
6223 type = state.getAttributedType(
6224 createSimpleAttr<ObjCInertUnsafeUnretainedAttr>(S.Context, attr),
6225 type, type);
6226 return true;
6227 }
6228
6229 QualType origType = type;
6230 if (!NonObjCPointer)
6231 type = S.Context.getQualifiedType(underlyingType);
6232
6233 // If we have a valid source location for the attribute, use an
6234 // AttributedType instead.
6235 if (AttrLoc.isValid()) {
6236 type = state.getAttributedType(::new (S.Context) ObjCOwnershipAttr(
6237 attr.getRange(), S.Context, II,
6238 attr.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()),
6239 origType, type);
6240 }
6241
6242 auto diagnoseOrDelay = [](Sema &S, SourceLocation loc,
6243 unsigned diagnostic, QualType type) {
6244 if (S.DelayedDiagnostics.shouldDelayDiagnostics()) {
6245 S.DelayedDiagnostics.add(
6246 sema::DelayedDiagnostic::makeForbiddenType(
6247 S.getSourceManager().getExpansionLoc(loc),
6248 diagnostic, type, /*ignored*/ 0));
6249 } else {
6250 S.Diag(loc, diagnostic);
6251 }
6252 };
6253
6254 // Sometimes, __weak isn't allowed.
6255 if (lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak &&
6256 !S.getLangOpts().ObjCWeak && !NonObjCPointer) {
6257
6258 // Use a specialized diagnostic if the runtime just doesn't support them.
6259 unsigned diagnostic =
6260 (S.getLangOpts().ObjCWeakRuntime ? diag::err_arc_weak_disabled
6261 : diag::err_arc_weak_no_runtime);
6262
6263 // In any case, delay the diagnostic until we know what we're parsing.
6264 diagnoseOrDelay(S, AttrLoc, diagnostic, type);
6265
6266 attr.setInvalid();
6267 return true;
6268 }
6269
6270 // Forbid __weak for class objects marked as
6271 // objc_arc_weak_reference_unavailable
6272 if (lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak) {
6273 if (const ObjCObjectPointerType *ObjT =
6274 type->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
6275 if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = ObjT->getInterfaceDecl()) {
6276 if (Class->isArcWeakrefUnavailable()) {
6277 S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_arc_unsupported_weak_class);
6278 S.Diag(ObjT->getInterfaceDecl()->getLocation(),
6279 diag::note_class_declared);
6280 }
6281 }
6282 }
6283 }
6284
6285 return true;
6286}
6287
6288/// handleObjCGCTypeAttr - Process the __attribute__((objc_gc)) type
6289/// attribute on the specified type. Returns true to indicate that
6290/// the attribute was handled, false to indicate that the type does
6291/// not permit the attribute.
6292static bool handleObjCGCTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state, ParsedAttr &attr,
6293 QualType &type) {
6294 Sema &S = state.getSema();
6295
6296 // Delay if this isn't some kind of pointer.
6297 if (!type->isPointerType() &&
6298 !type->isObjCObjectPointerType() &&
6299 !type->isBlockPointerType())
6300 return false;
6301
6302 if (type.getObjCGCAttr() != Qualifiers::GCNone) {
6303 S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_multiple_objc_gc);
6304 attr.setInvalid();
6305 return true;
6306 }
6307
6308 // Check the attribute arguments.
6309 if (!attr.isArgIdent(0)) {
6310 S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
6311 << attr << AANT_ArgumentString;
6312 attr.setInvalid();
6313 return true;
6314 }
6315 Qualifiers::GC GCAttr;
6316 if (attr.getNumArgs() > 1) {
6317 S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << attr
6318 << 1;
6319 attr.setInvalid();
6320 return true;
6321 }
6322
6323 IdentifierInfo *II = attr.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
6324 if (II->isStr("weak"))
6325 GCAttr = Qualifiers::Weak;
6326 else if (II->isStr("strong"))
6327 GCAttr = Qualifiers::Strong;
6328 else {
6329 S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)
6330 << attr.getName() << II;
6331 attr.setInvalid();
6332 return true;
6333 }
6334
6335 QualType origType = type;
6336 type = S.Context.getObjCGCQualType(origType, GCAttr);
6337
6338 // Make an attributed type to preserve the source information.
6339 if (attr.getLoc().isValid())
6340 type = state.getAttributedType(
6341 ::new (S.Context) ObjCGCAttr(attr.getRange(), S.Context, II,
6342 attr.getAttributeSpellingListIndex()),
6343 origType, type);
6344
6345 return true;
6346}
6347
6348namespace {
6349 /// A helper class to unwrap a type down to a function for the
6350 /// purposes of applying attributes there.
6351 ///
6352 /// Use:
6353 /// FunctionTypeUnwrapper unwrapped(SemaRef, T);
6354 /// if (unwrapped.isFunctionType()) {
6355 /// const FunctionType *fn = unwrapped.get();
6356 /// // change fn somehow
6357 /// T = unwrapped.wrap(fn);
6358 /// }
6359 struct FunctionTypeUnwrapper {
6360 enum WrapKind {
6361 Desugar,
6362 Attributed,
6363 Parens,
6364 Pointer,
6365 BlockPointer,
6366 Reference,
6367 MemberPointer
6368 };
6369
6370 QualType Original;
6371 const FunctionType *Fn;
6372 SmallVector<unsigned char /*WrapKind*/, 8> Stack;
6373
6374 FunctionTypeUnwrapper(Sema &S, QualType T) : Original(T) {
6375 while (true) {
6376 const Type *Ty = T.getTypePtr();
6377 if (isa<FunctionType>(Ty)) {
6378 Fn = cast<FunctionType>(Ty);
6379 return;
6380 } else if (isa<ParenType>(Ty)) {
6381 T = cast<ParenType>(Ty)->getInnerType();
6382 Stack.push_back(Parens);
6383 } else if (isa<PointerType>(Ty)) {
6384 T = cast<PointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType();
6385 Stack.push_back(Pointer);
6386 } else if (isa<BlockPointerType>(Ty)) {
6387 T = cast<BlockPointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType();
6388 Stack.push_back(BlockPointer);
6389 } else if (isa<MemberPointerType>(Ty)) {
6390 T = cast<MemberPointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType();
6391 Stack.push_back(MemberPointer);
6392 } else if (isa<ReferenceType>(Ty)) {
6393 T = cast<ReferenceType>(Ty)->getPointeeType();
6394 Stack.push_back(Reference);
6395 } else if (isa<AttributedType>(Ty)) {
6396 T = cast<AttributedType>(Ty)->getEquivalentType();
6397 Stack.push_back(Attributed);
6398 } else {
6399 const Type *DTy = Ty->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType();
6400 if (Ty == DTy) {
6401 Fn = nullptr;
6402 return;
6403 }
6404
6405 T = QualType(DTy, 0);
6406 Stack.push_back(Desugar);
6407 }
6408 }
6409 }
6410
6411 bool isFunctionType() const { return (Fn != nullptr); }
6412 const FunctionType *get() const { return Fn; }
6413
6414 QualType wrap(Sema &S, const FunctionType *New) {
6415 // If T wasn't modified from the unwrapped type, do nothing.
6416 if (New == get()) return Original;
6417
6418 Fn = New;
6419 return wrap(S.Context, Original, 0);
6420 }
6421
6422 private:
6423 QualType wrap(ASTContext &C, QualType Old, unsigned I) {
6424 if (I == Stack.size())
6425 return C.getQualifiedType(Fn, Old.getQualifiers());
6426
6427 // Build up the inner type, applying the qualifiers from the old
6428 // type to the new type.
6429 SplitQualType SplitOld = Old.split();
6430
6431 // As a special case, tail-recurse if there are no qualifiers.
6432 if (SplitOld.Quals.empty())
6433 return wrap(C, SplitOld.Ty, I);
6434 return C.getQualifiedType(wrap(C, SplitOld.Ty, I), SplitOld.Quals);
6435 }
6436
6437 QualType wrap(ASTContext &C, const Type *Old, unsigned I) {
6438 if (I == Stack.size()) return QualType(Fn, 0);
6439
6440 switch (static_cast<WrapKind>(Stack[I++])) {
6441 case Desugar:
6442 // This is the point at which we potentially lose source
6443 // information.
6444 return wrap(C, Old->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType(), I);
6445
6446 case Attributed:
6447 return wrap(C, cast<AttributedType>(Old)->getEquivalentType(), I);
6448
6449 case Parens: {
6450 QualType New = wrap(C, cast<ParenType>(Old)->getInnerType(), I);
6451 return C.getParenType(New);
6452 }
6453
6454 case Pointer: {
6455 QualType New = wrap(C, cast<PointerType>(Old)->getPointeeType(), I);
6456 return C.getPointerType(New);
6457 }
6458
6459 case BlockPointer: {
6460 QualType New = wrap(C, cast<BlockPointerType>(Old)->getPointeeType(),I);
6461 return C.getBlockPointerType(New);
6462 }
6463
6464 case MemberPointer: {
6465 const MemberPointerType *OldMPT = cast<MemberPointerType>(Old);
6466 QualType New = wrap(C, OldMPT->getPointeeType(), I);
6467 return C.getMemberPointerType(New, OldMPT->getClass());
6468 }
6469
6470 case Reference: {
6471 const ReferenceType *OldRef = cast<ReferenceType>(Old);
6472 QualType New = wrap(C, OldRef->getPointeeType(), I);
6473 if (isa<LValueReferenceType>(OldRef))
6474 return C.getLValueReferenceType(New, OldRef->isSpelledAsLValue());
6475 else
6476 return C.getRValueReferenceType(New);
6477 }
6478 }
6479
6480 llvm_unreachable("unknown wrapping kind");
6481 }
6482 };
6483} // end anonymous namespace
6484
6485static bool handleMSPointerTypeQualifierAttr(TypeProcessingState &State,
6486 ParsedAttr &PAttr, QualType &Type) {
6487 Sema &S = State.getSema();
6488
6489 Attr *A;
6490 switch (PAttr.getKind()) {
6491 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown attribute kind");
6492 case ParsedAttr::AT_Ptr32:
6493 A = createSimpleAttr<Ptr32Attr>(S.Context, PAttr);
6494 break;
6495 case ParsedAttr::AT_Ptr64:
6496 A = createSimpleAttr<Ptr64Attr>(S.Context, PAttr);
6497 break;
6498 case ParsedAttr::AT_SPtr:
6499 A = createSimpleAttr<SPtrAttr>(S.Context, PAttr);
6500 break;
6501 case ParsedAttr::AT_UPtr:
6502 A = createSimpleAttr<UPtrAttr>(S.Context, PAttr);
6503 break;
6504 }
6505
6506 attr::Kind NewAttrKind = A->getKind();
6507 QualType Desugared = Type;
6508 const AttributedType *AT = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Type);
6509 while (AT) {
6510 attr::Kind CurAttrKind = AT->getAttrKind();
6511
6512 // You cannot specify duplicate type attributes, so if the attribute has
6513 // already been applied, flag it.
6514 if (NewAttrKind == CurAttrKind) {
